title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in medium skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove to paper towels to drain.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Saute onion in drippings for 4 to 5 minutes. Add clam juice and potatoes.
Cover; cook over low heat until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Reserve a few pieces of bacon for garnish.
Add remaining bacon, minced clams, cream of celery soup, milk and pepper; cook over low heat until heated through.
Garnish with reserved bacon.
Serve with crackers, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed potato casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and cool; break into small pieces.
Set aside.
Mix parsley, onion, sour cream and mayonnaise together.
Refrigerate.
Wash potatoes well and dice into bite-sized pieces.
Boil for 10 minutes in salted water.
Drain well and pour into large mixing bowl.
Slice margarine onto hot potatoes.
Fold in the sour cream mixture and finally, add the bacon pieces.

title: yummy pumpkin bars
directions: Beat all ingredients until well mixed in a large bowl.	Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes.
Cool in pan then cover with the frosting and chopped walnuts (3/4 to 1 cup).

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix package of Good Seasons Mix with macaroni and vegetables and let stand over night in refrigerator.
A few hours before serving, pour Seven Seas Dressing over mixture and refrigerate.

title: beef-rice oriental
directions: Saute garlic in oil just until golden brown.
Add beef, rice, pepper and hot water; mix just to moisten rice.
Bring quickly to a boil over high heat, then cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Just before serving, add lettuce and soy sauce and toss lightly using 2 forks.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut bread into cubes.
Spread half the bread in pan.
Cut cream cheese into small cubes; sprinkle half over bread in pan.
Repeat layering with remaining bread and cream cheese.
Whisk eggs, milk and syrup in large bowl; pour over bread.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve warm with more syrup.

title: lots-of-eggs-bundt cake
directions: Grease a 12-cup Bundt pan and coat with sugar. Cream butter and sugar; add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour all at once and beat well. Add vanilla. Bake in the Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Cool at least 10 minutes. Then turn upside down on
a cake plate. Needs Cake Glaze but this cake is very good served with ice cream or fresh fruit or both.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Blend well.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Blend with squash mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry.
Drain juice from beans; mix beans, bacon and the rest of ingredients in a baking dish. Cover and bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: spaghetti(from the kitchen of leo schiller)
directions: Cook meat, onions, celery, green pepper and garlic 10 to 15 minutes in a large, heavy saucepan or Dutch oven, cutting meat apart with fork or spoon. Stir in brown sugar and other ingredients. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Spoon sauce over hot spaghetti and sprinkle generously with cheese.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1 layer of graham crackers in bottom of pan.
In a bowl, mix milk with French vanilla pudding.
Mix Cool Whip with pudding mixture.
Pour 1/2 pudding mix over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers; pour in rest of pudding mix and add one more layer of graham crackers.
Heat one plastic container of Duncan Hines Dutch fudge icing mix in microwave.
Drizzle over graham crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Line bottom of dish with cracker crumbs.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip and cover crumbs with 1/2 of mixture.
Add layer of cherry pie filling.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip and cream mixture.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.

title: taurean's no fail fudge
directions: Stir until melted; pour into buttered pan or platter.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 8 ingredients - chill for 24 hours, then salt and top with parmesan cheese

title: bean sandwich filling
directions: Mash 4 cups cooked pinto beans, leaving 1 cup whole.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve as sandwich spread or on lettuce bed as a salad.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 1 minute.
Add sugar and lemon juice, beating well.
Add soda, salt and spices.
Fold in flour and pumpkin until well combined.
Spread batter evenly onto a greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn cake out onto a towel that has been dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up towel with cake, jelly roll style and let cool.
When cool, unroll and spread with filling. Reroll cake without the towel.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: bubble bath
directions: Just mix and put in baby food jars.
Give as gifts.

title: lentil soup
directions: Mix all together.
Ready when lentils are tender.

title: quick and easy cookie bars
directions: Combine crackers, flour and soda; set aside.
Combine margarine and brown sugar and stir in eggs, water and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Immediately sprinkle remaining cup chocolate chips.
Let melt; spread over top.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Fry onion in oil until golden.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in tomato paste and juice.
Add seasonings and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: soft raisin filled cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and sour cream. Blend thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time until blended.
Chill overnight or at least 2 hours.
Roll out and cut with a 2-inch cookie cutter.
Put a teaspoon of filling, then top with another 2-inch circle of dough.
Seal around cookie.
Prick top of cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, make a stiff dough of the ingredients.
After making a stiff dough, grease another large bowl.
Put dough in it. Turn dough over so that all sides are oiled.
Cover lightly with oil and let stand overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Next morning, punch dough down and knead a little.
Divide into 3 parts and knead every part on a floured board a few times (8 to 10 times for each part).
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans and brush with oil. Let rise for 4 to 5 hours (all day is okay).
Dough rises very slowly.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion. Drain. Mix meat and rest of ingredients. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Put shell strips crisscross over top of pie.
Bake until done at 400°.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Place beans in 2-quart casserole.
Saute onion in bacon drippings in skillet.
Add bacon, sugar, catsup and vinegar. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together with some of the milk.
Then add enough milk to fill right amount in freezer.
Freeze.
(This recipe requires no eggs.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken pieces in water until tender.
Save broth.
Cut up chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Put half of stuffing in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Pour some broth over chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over casserole.
Put rest of stuffing mix on top and pour some more chicken broth over the whole thing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add well beaten eggs and milk.
Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and add to flour.
Combine all ingredients. Knead to a stiff dough.
Roll out thick or thin (I prefer thick) according to your preference.
Cut out with cookie or biscuit cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Blend fruit cocktail, cake mix and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in and sprinkle the coconut over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a deep dish 9-inch or regular 10-inch pie pan.
Combine in large mixing bowl flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, butter, egg and milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, but shrimp; mix well.
Fold in shrimp last.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; drop by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with sugar and nutmeg after baking.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pocket bread chicken - cheese filling
directions: Combine chicken, celery, parsley and lemon juice.
Mix milk, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Combine mixtures and chill.

title: fruities
directions: Mix well.
Press 3/4-inch thick in pan or mold into balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Mix soup with water.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup of the soup mixture, mix just to blend.
Shape into 18 meatballs.
Place in skillet.
Pour remaining soup mixture over meatballs.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes basting occasionally.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, rolled oats and baking powder.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of this into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread jam over this layer and cover jam with remaining crumb mixture.
Press down lightly.

title: german chocolate turtle bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/2 can of milk in a double boiler.
In a bowl, mix cake mix, oleo, rest of milk and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Take out and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour on caramel mixture and dab on remaining dough.
Bake for additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Cook peaches over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until tender (soft).
Add cinnamon, butter, vanilla, sugar and nutmeg. Mix well for another 5 minutes.
Pinch pieces off of refrigerated biscuit dough and drop into mixture.
Let simmer until biscuit dough (dumplings) are firm and fat, approximately 5 to 7 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: smothered cabbage
directions: In pot,
put oil and salt pork.
Brown (fry) salt pork. In a large
bowl
of
water,
add cabbage.
To salt pork, add cabbage, green onions, pepper
and the drippings from cabbage. (Should be enough water.
If
not, add 1/4 cup of water.) Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove
from
heat.
Take
top
off
or cabbage will overcook.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Arrange in a big vegetable platter the carrot sticks, sliced cucumbers, broccoli, cauliflower, cherry tomatoes, celery sticks and mushrooms (can substitute with green onions, olives and pickles).
Mix the cottage cheese, sour cream and dressing.
Pour the dip in a deep dish and arrange in the center of a platter.

title: caraotas(venezuelan black beans)
directions: Soak the beans overnight in water with baking soda.
Add the green pepper and one of the onions to the beans and boil for 2 hours.
Then remove the green pepper and onion.
Mix the chopped onion with the garlic and brown in corn oil.
Pour the browned mixture into the beans and boil for 15 minutes.
Mash some beans to thicken the sauce.
Serve as soup or side dish with white rice. Bay leaf, laurel and cumin may be added to taste, also more garlic.

title: cherry cream whip
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick margarine or butter. Line Pyrex oblong dish with crumb mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine and beat with mixer until well blended. Add 2 heads cauliflower, 1 can black olives(sliced), 1 small jar pimentos and any amount of green or red peppers, onions, carrots, celery or any other vegetables that are desired.
Mix everything together and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: apple dip(great for kid's party)
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put nuts in blender to chop. Slice apples and to keep them from turning brown dip in lemon. Dip slices in cream cheese mixture then coat with nuts.
Tastes like candy apples.

title: coconut crisps
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Set aside. In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour mixture, vanilla, oats, then coconut.
Drop by teaspoons 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: santa's snickers brand surprises
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, and sugars using a mixer on medium to low speed until light and fluffy. Slowly add eggs and vanilla until thoroughly combined. Then mix in flour, salt and baking soda. Cover and chill dough for 2-3 hours. Unwrap all the miniatures. Remove dough from refrigerator. Divide into 1 Tbsp. pieces and flatten. Place a miniature in the center of each piece of dough. Form the dough into a ball around each Snickers. Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 10-12 minutes. Let cookies cool on baking rack or wax paper.

title: low-fat banana nut bread
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add sugars; beat well after each addition. Add bananas; mix well. Stir in baking mix and pecans. Pour into greased 9 X 5 X 3 inch loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool completely.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring juice and enough water to boil to make 1 3/4 cups of hot liquid.
Mix cherry gelatin until it dissolves.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well and chill until set.
Makes a very attractive Christmas salad.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in order.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted. Serve warm or cold.
May be served with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake crust. Put cocoa, 1 cup sugar and flour in a pot. Mix with spoon very well. Divide the eggs. Beat the yolks and add to dry ingredients. Mix well. Then add the milk. Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir. Put in baked pie shell.

title: one hour hot rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add yeast, dissolved in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, soda and flour (all sifted together). Add oil and beat well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Knead, then roll and cut with cutter.
Butter pan; set for 30 minutes and butter tops.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: jennie's brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken in pressure cooker and bone.
Cook other ingredients in black pot for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Add water as necessary.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and sugar.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Lay in 10 x 14-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix 1 can cream of celery soup, 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 soup can of milk.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle 1 package Pepperidge Farm dressing mix on top. Pour 1 cup chicken stock with 1 stick margarine melted over dressing.
Bake at 350° about 2 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: a cake for mother
directions: Mix well, bake in a hearty, warm oven and serve to "Mother" every day.
She ought to have it in big slices.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain off fat.
Add onions; cook until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat through.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Cover; bake 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Break into pieces.
Add salt, pepper, tomato juice, onions (chopped), sugar, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
Simmer until thick.
Makes enough for 20 buns.

title: almond crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Grease bundt pan and dust with breadcrumbs. Melt the butter. Add almonds, sugar, corn syrup and almond extract. Stir until the sugar dissolves, 2 minutes. Pour into prepared pan.

title: pineapple-coconut drops
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and ginger; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and shortening with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture; beat well. Stir in coconut, pineapple and nuts.

title: orange nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill until firm.

title: crowd chicken casserole
directions: Combine the first six ingredients.
Add 2 cups cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; add to chicken mixture and toss.
Spoon into two greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Sprinkle with chips.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Yields 24 servings.

title: oatmeal hermits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients in to a boil in saucepan.
Cook covered until soft.
Puree in blender.
Saute onion with salt in butter until translucent.
Add celery and celery seed.
Saute until tender.
Whisk milk, sour cream and pepper into soup, about 10 minutes.

title: roast gobbler
directions: Salt and pepper turkey.
Place celery and half of onion in body cavity.
Mix butter and soy sauce, baste breasts, legs and thighs. Place on a rack in a large pan and cover loosely with foil.
In an iron skillet, make a roux with oil and flour.
Chop remaining onion and saute in roux until limp.
Add chicken broth to make gravy, then pour over turkey.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes per pound, basting every half hour.
If you stuff with dressing, increase time to 25 minutes per pound.
If the bird is to be carved ahead of time, cover with the gravy to keep moist.
Serves 15.

title: anise cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar
well;
add well beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add milk,
anise
oil, flour, salt and baking powder, a little at a time.
Freeze dough for several hours or chill overnight.
Roll
thin; cut with cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake
on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: homemade peach crisp
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Mix the other ingredients together and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake till golden brown in pre-heated oven at 350°.

title: lazy daisy dessert
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Combine flour and baking powder. Combine butter, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour mixture and butter mixture alternately with egg mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
A jelly roll pan works good.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat eggs lightly and combine with other ingredients.
Pour into greased mold and bake 25 minutes in a pan of hot water in moderate oven.
Serve hot, garnished with parsley and lemon slices.

title: whole fried okra
directions: Dip okra in beaten eggs, then in cheese mixture and back in egg mixture, then in flour and meal.
Deep fry until slightly browned.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a large baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 1/2 hour.

title: delicious steamed collard greens
directions: Prepare collard greens.
Chop collard greens small.
Bring water, smoked ham pieces or bacon strips to a boil.
Add collard greens and steam for 15 minutes.
Add salt and sugar.
Steam for 45 minutes; stir frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in olive oil.
Add onion, cook until tender. Stir in other ingredients
in
order
given
except olives and cheese. Bring the mixture to
a
boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into baking dish and top with cheese.
Broil
until
cheese
is
melted and garnish with stuffed olives.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut up into pieces, place in casserole dish.
Add rest of ingredients, except for chips.
Heat thoroughly, usually 30 to 40 minutes.
Crumble potato chips on top at end of cooking time.
Brown slightly and serve over rice.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl; beat on low for 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brown
and
scramble sausage; saute pepper, onion and celery
in
tablespoon
oil until tender. Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish and bake, covered, for about 1 hour and 25 minutes for
raw rice.
If
using
Minute
rice, bake for 45 minutes. Serves 10.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Pour over any kind of fresh, chopped fruit.
This makes an excellent and tasty dessert, especially after a "hearty" meal or luncheon-type meal.

title: busy season casserole
directions: Fry cubed steak and then put in a casserole dish.
Add a layer of carrots.
Add a layer of potatoes.
Salt each layer.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: turkey-taco salad
directions: Spray 10-inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray and heat over medium heat.
Add turkey and, using back of a wooden spoon to crumble meat, cook, stirring occasionally, until turkey is browned and cooked through, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add water and taco seasonings mix and stir to combine thoroughly.
Bring liquid to boil.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage 'n noodle dinner
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain.
Brown sausage and pour of grease.
Add noodles, peas, juice and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: baked ham and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine honey, butter, green pepper, soy sauce and mustard; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly to mix well.
Turn into lightly greased 2-quart casserole; bake, covered, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and make well in center.
Set aside. Combine milk, oil and eggs.
Pour in well and add bananas.
Stir (don't beat) until moist.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stacey's strawberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup of the ripest strawberries, sugar and 3/4 cup water.
Puree. Boil in microwave.

title: diabetic cream puffs
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine water, shortening and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour, beating constantly until smooth and pulls away from side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat vigorously after each egg.
Drop on cookie sheet by spoonful and allow for expansion.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 25 minutes more.
Cool and fill with NutraSweet pudding.

title: easy wine pork chops
directions: Brown chops in heavy skillet.
Season with salt and pepper. Add the wine to half cover the meat.
Arrange onions around chops. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour or until meat is fork-tender.
Add more wine as needed.
Serves 6.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and flour.
Add nutmeg with sugar. Pour into bowl with eggs and sugar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Dot the top with butter.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour; then turn to 200° and bake until crust is brown and pie is set.

title: roulade
directions: Spread mustard on each steak.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Lay slice of bacon on each steak, then onion and one dill spear per steak.
Roll up tight and secure with toothpick or sewing thread. Saute in fat on all sides.
Add water and cook until tender. Thicken juices with flour to thicken for gravy.
Serve with "Red Cabbage and Potatoes."

title: mama's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add vanilla. Sift flour and blend in creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet. Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: beer boiled shrimp with fettuccine
directions: Fill large pot 1/2 full with water and beer and tablespoon of Zatarain's crab and shrimp boil and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Toss in shrimp; cover and turn off heat.
After 4 minutes, drain shrimp and rinse with cold water to stop cooking process. Melt butter in a saucepan and add in heavy cream.
Add 4 to 5 dashes of Tabasco.
Toss shrimp with fettuccine and pour sauce over top.
Grind black pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and refrigerate.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft.
Mix pizza sauce and topping(s) of choice in bowl.
Cut potato to butterfly opening while hot and spread pizza sauce mixture on open-faced potato.
Top with desired amount of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: carrot spice nibbles
directions: Cream butter and add sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Cook noodles until tender, drain and rinse.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.
Layer 1/2 noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with 1/2 Ricotta filling; add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt. Beat together
eggs,
oil and vanilla.
Mix together carrots, apples, nuts, raisins and
coconut.
Mix
all
three
together just until incorporated
(don't
overmix).
Spoon
into
paper muffin cups or greased and
floured muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: fried sweet potato slices
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes lengthwise in 1/4 inch thick slices.
Heat the butter and oil in a skillet.
Place potato slices in skillet and cook until lightly brown on each side.
They should be fork tender after browning. Place on absorbent paper and sprinkle generously with sugar on both sides.
These are easy to make and surprisingly delicious.

title: spinach soup
directions: Brown sausage (remove casing), onion and garlic.
Add tomato paste.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Cook until carrots are soft. Any favorite vegetable(s) may be added.

title: creamy broccoli or mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Place in casserole.
Beat soup and milk until smooth. Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix biscuit mix with margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp and chicken florentine
directions: Cook chicken and chop.
Cook shrimp and peel and cut in half lengthwise and sprinkle with garlic, pepper and white wine.

title: real fudge brownies
directions: Mix together in order.
For fudge like brownies, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix together and cook in 9 x 13-inch floured and greased baking dish.
Allow to cool 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour holes in cake with metal skewer.
Mix 1 cup powdered sugar, grated rind and juice of 1 lemon.
Pour over cooled cake.

title: golden lemon cheese pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla extract. Stir or use mixer until well blended.
Pour in pie crust and put in refrigerator for a few hours before serving.

title: muffins
directions: Mix well.
Put in muffin tins.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes at 350°.

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Form balls and dip in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers) and place in greased casserole dish.
Roll Ritz crackers finely and sprinkle on top; dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal-fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix sugar, 3/4 cup margarine, the eggs and vanilla.
Mix in baking mix and oats; reserve.
Heat chips, milk, 2 tablespoons margarine and the salt in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.

title: oatmeal crispies(excellent)
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to first mix.
Make into rolls and refrigerate.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Melt butter in a shallow oblong baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not mix.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl until softened; beat in sugar. Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut, whipped topping and extract.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm. Garnish with Angel Flake toasted coconut.
Let stand at room temperature to soften before serving.

title: baked chicken or turkey salad
directions: Put in large shallow 1 1/2-quart baking pan.
Sprinkle with potato chips and cheese. Chill several hours or overnight.
Bake 25 minutes at 400° or until heated.
Serves 8.

title: low calorie lemon sauced salmon
directions: Combine yogurt, lemon zest, parsley, marjoram and salt.
Chill 1 hour.
Brush salmon steaks with lemon juice.
Broil about 4 inches from heat source in a preheated broiler for 10 minutes. There is no need to turn the steaks over.
During broiling, baste occasionally with lemon juice.
Serve steaks with yogurt sauce spooned over each one.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook noodles according to box directions. Heat sauce and combine with hamburger and sausage. In an 11x13 in. pan, sprayed with Pam, layer noodles and sauce. Top layer with pepperoni, onions and green peppers, mushrooms and cheeses. Make about three layers and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: delicious egg rolls *(not chinese)
directions: Combine in a saucepan milk, water and sugar.
Heat until barely warm.
Remove from heat and add crumbled yeast cake.
Beat eggs thoroughly and add to milk mixture.
Add enough flour to make a thin batter.
Add shortening and enough flour to make a soft dough, about 4 cups.
Refrigerate freshly mixed dough for several hours to chill. Punch down and shape into rolls.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours before baking at 425°.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat 1/2 inch oil in large skillet.
Cook chicken over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes. Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes and brown.

title: cocoa fudge sauce
directions: Combine the water and sugar in a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat and stir to dissolve the sugar.
Increase the heat and bring to a rolling boil to form a sugar syrup.
Let the syrup boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and whisk in cocoa powder.
Return pan to medium heat and whisk 3 to 5 minutes until sauce is smooth and thick.
Remove from heat and whisk in the vanilla.

title: omelet
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick. Stir in flour and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and add seasonings.
Pour into well-greased round skillet. Cook over low flame until well puffed and slightly brown on bottom. Omelet should be firm when touched at this stage.
Complete cooking process in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Serve at once.

title: barbecue
directions: In large skillet brown green pepper and onion.
Add ground beef.
Brown beef, slowly crumbling with a fork.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients with beef.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pork chops with golden mushroom soup
directions: Brown chops.
Remove from pot.
Add golden mushroom soup with 1/4 cup of water, onion, celery, carrots, garlic salt and pepper. Return chops to pot.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes until tender.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix as written down.
Put in refrigerator to chill about 1/2 hour, then roll in balls.
Mash down balls with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie rack.

title: mystery pie
directions: Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
Freezes well.

title: "cracker barrel hash brown casserole"
directions: Place in a sprayed pan, 9 x 13, adding the hash browns last. Cook, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave enchilada torte
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Add salsa and chili powder. Layer 4 tortillas in 2 qt. Microwave safe dish. Top with half of the meat mixture and half of the soup. Repeat layers. Top with cheese. Cover. Microwave at 70 percent power for 8 min. or until hot. Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: manicotti
directions: Boil manicotti shells until tender.
Brown and drain ground beef and sausage.
Mix together with 1/2 pound cheese, egg, bread, milk and spices.
Cover bottom of a baking dish with spaghetti sauce.
Stuff shells with mixture and place in dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbles.

title: apple butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Combine soda and apple butter.
Stir well and add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Add nuts and cherries.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet, not too closely because they will spread.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Form hamburger into small balls.
Place on bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Slice potatoes over meatballs.
Add onions, sliced 1/4 inch thick over potatoes.
Combine milk with cream of chicken soup.
Mix and pour over ingredients in dish.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Use 1/3 cup mix for each cup boiling water.
Makes 45 to 50 cups.
Great to put in gift jars for neighbors at Christmas.

title: polish dill pickles
directions: Cover bottom of 8-gallon crock with dill.
Put cucumbers in; add allspice, garlic and red peppers.
Bring to a boil 2 gallons water, vinegar and salt.

Boil 5 minutes, let cool to room temperature, pour over cucumbers, put dill on top until cucumbers are covered with dill, and put plate on top so pickles won't float. Put small stone on top to keep pickles under brine.
(Be sure stone is not heavy enough to smash the pickles.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Line casserole with ham or chipped beef, then chicken breasts .
Mix together the sour cream and soup; pour over the chicken.
Top with almonds.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook beef and bacon until all pink is gone. Drain.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Put mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole, lightly greased.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture, one egg at a time, mixing well.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Freeze according to your ice cream freezer's directions.

title: ricotta doughnut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use teaspoon to drop batter in hot oil.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towel.
Cool a little.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: date pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Good with sliced apples, peaches, strawberries and any other fruit suitable for dipping.

title: trifle
directions: Break half the sponge cake in bottom of a glass bowl.
Cover with half the raspberries, half the peaches, vanilla pudding and Cool Whip (mix almond extract with Cool Whip).
Break the other half of the sponge cake and layer all again, putting sliced kiwi on top.

title: southern boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs; mix with sugar.
Pour into a double boiler with warm milk.
Cook about 10 or 12 minutes.
You can make as many cookies as you like, but do not double recipe.
Strain through cheesecloth.

title: ma's dill pickles
directions: In sterilized jars, start with dill and onion pieces, then a layer of cucumbers.
Add more layers until 1/2 inch from top, ending with dill and onions.
Add a few pieces of alum to each jar. In a large pan, bring vinegar, water and salt to a rolling boil. Fill jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Wipe clean and seal with lids and covers.
Years ago lids sealed easily, now it may be necessary to "hot bath" them.
If this is necessary, I bring the water just to a boil then remove.
I do not "cook" them.
Save leftover brine for next time or use for chunk pickles.
Using an ice cream bucket fill as jars and store in the refrigerator.
I use this for larger pieces or leftover cucumbers.
This is my grandmother's recipe.
We love 'em!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well in order given.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Nuts may be added if desired.
Bake at 375°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients and pour over cereal.
Cool a little and pour powdered sugar over mix.
Put in large covered bowl and shake to coat.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thinly slice onion.
Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Layer potatoes and onions in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Wash peppers and cut into rings (removing seeds).
Arrange on top of potatoes.
Slice sausage and place on top.
Cover and bake about 1 hour, until potatoes are tender. Remove cover and bake about 15 minutes longer to brown sausage.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix with all other ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan to bake.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Melt one stick of oleo and dribble over top; sprinkle 2 cups of cornflakes over oleo.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: blueberry pineapple cream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Toast corn flakes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine butter and sugar; pour over cereal and stir until evenly coated.
Reserve 3 tablespoons for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan; refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Let water, shortening and salt come to a boil and melt shortening.
Reduce heat to warm and add self-rising flour all at one time.
Stir hard until it makes a ball around the spoon.
Take off heat and add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating in each egg thoroughly with a spoon.
Drop by tablespoons on one greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 325° and bake another 20 minutes.
Let puffs cool.
Cut off tops.
Fill with filling, replace tops, then put icing on top.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in milk in a small saucepan over low heat.
Add butter, salt, thyme and pepper; cool slightly.
Combine turkey, bread crumbs, celery, onion and parsley.
Combine bouillon mixture and eggs; add to turkey mixture.
Mix lightly until blended.
Place mixture in a greased 1 1/2-quart loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately an hour or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Slice and serve with hot cranberry sauce.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix all these ingredients together by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
I put mine in muffin cups in cupcake holders and freeze.
Then put in Ziploc bags and use when you need only one or two servings.

title: j.t.'s cheesecake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and press in 9-inch spring-form pan; freeze.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Beat in yolks, one at at time.
Add sugar, lemon juice, vanilla, lemon peel and cinnamon and blend until smooth.
Whip 4 egg whites until stiff peaks form, stir in one large spoonful to cream cheese mix; fold in remaining. Pour in crust.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Mix topping.
Bake for 15 minutes more.
Chill.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and mix in pineapple in double boiler.
Add jello and allow to cool until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in cream.
Whip with powdered sugar.
Fold into crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and put into freezer.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until translucent. Deglaze with wine; reduce (about 5 minutes).
Add clam juice; reduce about 5 minutes.
Add basil, salt, pepper and lemon juice. Thicken sauce with diluted cornstarch.
Add clam mix.
Do not cook after adding clams.
Serve over linguine or preferred pasta.

title: nacho grande
directions: Brown your meat and add green onions.
Drain fat.
Add refried beans to meat and simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.
While this is simmering, melt your Velveeta and Ro-Tel.
Chop up lettuce, tomatoes and black olives.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Ritz crackers may be substituted for bread crumbs and margarine.

title: fried catfish
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, cayenne pepper and garlic powder.
Coat catfish with the mixture, shaking off excess.
Fill deep pot or 12-inch skillet half full with vegetable oil.
Heat to 350°.
Add catfish in single layer and fry until golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes, depending on size.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil and chop chicken. Melt butter in large skillet. Saute onion, celery, garlic and flour; stir. Add soup, milk, pimento, mushrooms, water chestnuts, olives, lemon pepper, sherry and cheese. Cook noodles in broth; drain and rinse in cold water. Mix together. Bake in 2 large baking dishes. Add 2 teaspoons sherry on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, soften yeast in warm water.
Mix in potato flakes, sugar, melted margarine, salt, eggs, peel and raisins.
Add flour until dough is no longer sticky, about 7 1/2 cups.
Knead with dough hook 2 to 3 minutes or by hand 10 minutes until smooth.
Put dough in a large, greased bowl, turning it once so it is greased on the top and bottom.
Cover bowl with a towel.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add sour cream, onion, carrot, margarine (melted), chicken soup and crumbs. Stir together.
Place in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs or Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread by package directions, cool. When cooled crumble and add the onion, pepper, corn and tomatoes. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together and fold into the cornbread mixture. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bacon bits.

title: chickpea sauce and spaghetti(low-fat)
directions: In a blender or food processor, puree 1 can of the chickpeas (garbanzo beans) with its liquid.

In a large saucepan, heat the oil and saute the garlic and onion until garlic starts to brown. Add the tomatoes, their liquid, rosemary, chickpea puree and the remaining can of chickpeas with its liquid.
Heat the mixture for 15 minutes or until thickened; stir often.
Add the parsley and pepper.
Toss the hot cooked spaghetti with the sauce and sprinkle it with Parmesan before serving.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 2 small loaves. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
In large pan, mix remaining ingredients with hamburger and onion, except for cheese and tortillas.
In 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam), place 2 tortillas in bottom; add half of burger mixture.
Place 2 more tortillas and top with remaining hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; spread Cheddar cheese on top and leave in oven until cheese melts.

title: pear bread pudding
directions: Greased 9x9 inch baked dish.

title: wild rice and shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package, using 1/4 cup less water.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bbq meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shortening, and shape into small balls.
Place in shallow pan with shortening; fry until done. Meatballs can also be placed in an aluminium covered pan and baked at 350° for 15 minutes in the oven.

title: creme de menthe dessert
directions: Crush large package of Oreo cookies, less icing.
Melt oleo. Mix with Oreo crumbs.
Pat in rectangular baking dish for crust. Reserve 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top.
Mix ice cream with sherbet (softened).
Add cream de menthe and Cool Whip.
May add green food coloring.
Pour over Oreo crust.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Freeze; cut in squares.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in cold water.
Add strawberries and pineapple; stir until strawberries separate; mix well.
Pour mixture into a baking dish; chill until set but not firm.
Combine rest of ingredients and blend until smooth.
Spread over gelatin layer.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: baked chicken in savory crumbs
directions: Arrange chicken snugly in shallow baking pan. Pour butter over chicken. Combine bread crumb and seasonings and sprinkle over chicken. Bake, uncovered, one hour at 350°. Serves 4.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute salt pork and onions.
Add in pot tomatoes, potatoes, corn, milk, and salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour on low.
Serve with crackers.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Blend butter or margarine with 1/2 cup sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in nutmeg, vanilla, croutons and corn flakes.
Place half of the mixture in greased, shallow baking dish. Arrange rhubarb evenly over top and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and remaining creamed mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until rhubarb is done.

title: hawaiian chicken over rice
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes uncovered.
Serve over rice.

title: one egg pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix lard, egg, sugar and milk until relatively smooth; add flour to thicken to cakelike batter.
Pour into a greased cast-iron skillet or baking pan.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until done by toothpick test.
Serve with strawberries and whipped cream or hot chocolate sauce.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, mix oil, eggs and vanilla; add to flour mixture and beat.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Fold in nuts. Bake in three well-greased 9-inch baking pans.
Let stand 10 minutes, then remove from pans.
Frost with cream cheese frosting. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice until well blended.
Add strawberries and pecans.
Mix well and then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and chill.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: my own chicken cream cheese roll
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature. Mix with mayonnaise.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Form into a roll.
Roll in pecans.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: magic fudge
directions: Place chocolate morsels in 1-quart glass measure or casserole. Heat in microwave (Medium setting) for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until melted.
Stir once during melting, stir until smooth.
Blend in milk, vanilla and salt.
Add nuts.
Turn mixture into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm, cut into 1 inch squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: nana hill's fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Simmer lightly 15 to 20 minutes.
Take pan off heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat with wooden spoon until thick.
Pour into greased pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: scalloped broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender-crisp; drain well and chop into small pieces.
Discard tough pieces of stem.
Place broccoli in bowl; add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in egg; add crackers and spices.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cut ham into strips about 4 1/2 inches long and about 3/4-inch wide.
Place small amount of softened cream cheese on ham strip. Put 1 slice of green onion into cream cheese and roll.
Hold together with toothpick.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box. Saut chopped pepper and onions in margarine until tender. Mix in large skillet Ro-Tel with onions and pepper and cook for about 3 minutes. Add cream of mushroom soup. Add drained crawfish and cook for about 5 minutes. In large casserole, spread rice on bottom. Pour crawfish mixture over rice and spread evenly. Sprinkle Tony's Creole over this and then sprinkle cheese over rest. Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: marinated fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruit and mix the liquid juices together. Divide juice in half; set aside.
Mix all fruit except bananas in a separate bowl.
Mix orange drink and pudding mix together; add 1/2 of the liquid fruit juice to the dry mixture.
Add more juice if needed (mixture should be creamy but not thick).
Add pudding to fruit; fold together.
Chill.
Just before serving, add bananas.

title: taco casserole(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine stuffing, corn and 1/2 C water; stir well.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; set aside.
Cook meat and onion in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well; return to pan.
Add remaining 1/2 C water, beans, salsa, and seasoning; stir well.
Spoon meat mixture over stuffing mixture; top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Cut into squares.

title: turkey crunch
directions: Mix all together except noodles.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with noodles.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, add sugar and let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple and marshmallows, fold in Cool Whip. Put in several small containers and freeze.
Makes 30 servings.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Once potatoes have been baked, scoop out inside.
Mix with cream cheese, level tablespoon of butter and enough milk to whip smooth.
Parsley flakes can be added, as desired.
Put potato mixture back in the potato shells; sprinkle with paprika to garnish.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Brown sausage and drain grease.
Place sausage on bread.
Cover sausage with shredded cheese.
Mix together eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats.
Let stand 10 minutes. Cream both sugars and butter together.
Add mix with oatmeal mixture.
Add 2 eggs, also dry ingredients.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 375° until ready.

title: ramen salad
directions: Mix together slaw and onions. Add Ramen noodles.

title: punch
directions: Blend together lemonade, strawberries and instant tea.
Add sugar and water. Blend.
Refrigerate until served.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage, onion and green pepper until browned; drain off excess fat.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage mixture over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
(I sometimes put mushrooms or pepperoni on top). Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry buckle bread
directions: Beat 3/4 cup sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together 2 cups of the flour and milk alternately to beaten mixture.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with blueberries.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; cut in margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add salt, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Place over low heat; stir until steam rises.
Remove from heat and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 15 minutes or until firm.
Never gets watery.

title: butter cookies
directions: Work flour, butter and salt together.
Add egg yolks and sour cream.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator at least 4 hours or overnight.
Roll out and cut into squares.
Fill with apricots, prune butter or nuts.
Fold two corners to center.
Press lightly. Brush with beaten egg whites.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in the margarine.
Add the hominy, cream of mushroom soup, and cheese whiz.
Stir until cheese is melted. Place in 13 x 9 pan and cover with crushed Fritos.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Blend together sugar, flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt. Beat for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and Miracle Whip.
Mix well. Then slowly add warm water (not hot).
Beat until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cocoa; gradually add milk.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Cool. Store in refrigerator.
Serve over ice cream, hot or cold.

title: quick pate-stuffed french bread
directions: In large bowl beat cheese with ham until blended.
Stir in onions, parsley, pimiento and relish.
Cut 1 inch from each end of bread.
With long serrated knife carefully hollow out bread, leaving about 1/4 inch shell all around.
Stuff cheese mixture into bread.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: yum-yums
directions: Place melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour the graham cracker crumbs over the butter. Stir until crumbs are coated with butter.
Press the crumbs down so they cover the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle half of the chocolate bits over the crumbs.
Sprinkle the butterscotch bits on top.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate bits.
Pour the condensed milk evenly over the mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is golden brown and lightly bubbly.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: upside-down pie
directions: In a heavy frypan, fry onions in 2 tablespoons shortening until soft.
Add hamburg and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Mix as for biscuits the flour, baking powder, salt, shortening, paprika, celery, celery salt and milk.
Use grated cheese if desired. Spoon on top of hamburg mixture in frypan.
Bake at 475° for 20 minutes.
Turn upside down on platter when done.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Combine cream cheese and butter. Mix spinach with cream cheese and butter.
Add seasonings.
Put in greased baking dish.
Cover generously with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: uncle tom's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onions together.
Drain off grease if you ain't done it already.
Go to Aldi's and buy your chili beans, salt, pepper, chili powder, hot sauce, soy sauce, onions, seasoned salt and/or steak sauce.
You're going to be in misery, so make sure it's not over spending too much money.
If you can, go to Mark Bailey's Discount and buy your steak sauce...1 gal. of Heinz for $4.99,
it's good!
Drain off the juice from the tomatoes and discard tomatoes (or eat them by themselves). Remember, this is chili, not tomato soup.
Mix all together, bring to a boil and simmer 30-45 minutes.
Get your crackers at Aldi's too.

title: make-your-own syrup
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the jam and water.
Stir and boil together for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve hot or cold on pancakes, oatmeal or ice cream.

title: dale's delightful hot chocolate
directions: Other brands may be substituted, but will not taste as good.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Beat eggs for 1 minute.
Blend flour, sugar, Crisco, milk and eggs.
Then beat 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lone star caviar
directions: Soak peas in enough water to cover for 6 hours.
Drain well. Place peas in saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and boil for 45 minutes.
Blend in dressing and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Serve as a salad.

title: raspberry white chocolate soup
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Puree and serve chilled in soup bowls.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, water, salt and paprika.
Heat until sugar dissolves, then let cool.
Combine all other ingredients and pour sugar mixture over them and let marinate overnight.
Drain 2 hours before serving and enjoy.

title: potato pies(fatayer batata)
directions: Shred potatoes and add pinch of salt to draw moisture.
Saute beef in 1/4 pound butter.
Grate onion.
Squeeze all moisture from potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and season to taste.
Place on dough patties and close.
Fry in clarified butter for about 2 minutes on each side.
Serve hot or cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Add cheese (cut in chunks) and let melt.
Put broccoli and cheese in casserole dish.
Add crushed cracker crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Dredge tomatoes in mix on both sides to coat them well.
Use enough shortening to make 1/4-inch depth when heated in skillet.
Heat skillet to medium-high.
Fry tomatoes a few at a time, without touching each other, about 2 minutes on each side.
They should be golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: yellow punch
directions: Heat 1 quart of water to boiling.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 2 gallons.
Put into containers; refrigerate overnight.
Mix 1 gallon of this with 1 quart of ginger ale and serve.
Makes around 50 cups.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into 9 x 14 pan.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour this batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Add peaches.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easter cake frosting
directions: Beat together the confectioners sugar, butter, milk or cream and lemon extract until smooth.
Add the egg whites and beat until light.
Frost the layers and sides of cake.

title: duchess vegetables
directions: Spoon mashed potatoes into a 9-inch pie plate, building up the edge to form a shell.
Place carrots in a row across the middle. Spoon green beans on each side.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and marjoram (salt is unnecessary).
Dot with butter.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until vegetables are hot.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Pop microwave popcorn.
Put in brown grocery bag, picking out unpopped kernels.
Bring to boil in microwave all ingredients (except popcorn and soda).
Cook at full power for 2 minutes.
Let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add soda.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour over popcorn in grocery bag and shake well.
Put grocery bag in microwave for 1 minute.
Remove and shake again. Microwave 1 more minute.
Pour onto wax paper and spread out or pour into large bowl and stir until cooled.

title: aunt lucy's spanish rice
directions: Melt shortening; brown garlic and onion slightly.
Add meat and brown.
Add pepper, celery, tomato juice and seasonings. Cover and cook until steaming.
Stir mixture and sprinkle rice over top.
Do not stir after adding rice.
Cover; turn heat to low.
Cook, without removing cover, for 30 minutes.
Remove lid and cook another 15 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender and store in refrigerator.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In large pot, cook celery and onion in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients except noodles and parsley.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add noodles and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Beat egg; add milk.
Crumble in bread.
Mix until well blended.
Add ground beef and onion.
Sprinkle in salt and pepper. Add Sloppy Joes mix and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls of desired size.
Place in lightly greased casserole.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: lemon curd
directions: Combine ingredients in the top of a double boiler. Stir over the simmering water until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking and stirring until curd thickens. If desired, strain out lemon rind before serving. Serve on shortbread, toast, ice cream, muffins, cakes. Store refrigerated.

title: reuben ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Chill until firm. Garnish by rolling in parsley.
Serve with rye crackers.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar; let come to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello and water.
Mix well and refrigerate until it thickens.
Add cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.
Fold until well mixed. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in one glass of water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add salt, sugar, oil and remainder of water.
Add first two sifters of flour.
Can be stirred in with a spoon.
Then knead until it is not sticky.
May have to add more flour.
Cover with Crisco and let rise until doubled in bowl.
Knead down.
Divide into 3 equal loaves.
Put in 3 bread pans and again cover with light coat of Crisco.
When doubled in size bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes.
Turn out on cooling rack.
For a tough crust, dampen crust with water.

title: good liver!
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crush.
Brown onion and pepper in bacon fat or butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over liver in baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas several hours; drain.
Add cold water, pork and onion.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours; rub through sieve.
Add butter and flour cooked together.
Salt and pepper.
Dilute with milk or water.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Put cream cheese on the bottom of a deep bowl.
Pour marshmallows over top.
Pour pineapple evenly over to completely cover marshmallows.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Pour in Cool Whip and beat until marshmallows are soft and fairly melted.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook chicken with enough water to cover until tender.
Remove bones and skin.
Prepare stuffing using chicken broth (2 cups) and eliminating butter.
Spread stuffing in an 8 x 11-inch pan. Spread chicken pieces on top.
Cook broccoli until tender (drain) and lay on top of chicken.

title: t. j.'s homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly. Add Milnot, Eagle Brand milk and milk.
Freeze.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until soft enough to mash.
Add onion and all other ingredients, except crumbs and butter.
Put in greased casserole dish; sprinkle top with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vicki's deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Mash yolk and mix with mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well with fork and refill egg whites.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: nachos and hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave and put cheese, salsa and hamburger in crock-pot on high setting.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed well.
Let simmer.
Serve over nachos.

title: chicken mexicana
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Arrange in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave at High for 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is done.
Cool.
Cut chicken into smaller pieces, if desired.
Combine chicken soup, cheese soup, tomatoes and green chilies.
Layer half of chips and all of chicken in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Microwave at High for 10 to 12 minutes, turning dish after 5 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top and microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 additional minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Put in plastic bag.
Add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Shake until covered. Grease tube pan and pour nuts in bottom. Add biscuits.
Melt butter and brown sugar. Pour on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello.
Let cool.
Cream package of cream cheese, then add jello mixture, nuts and drained pineapple.
Store in refrigerator. Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Break eggs into bowl and beat slightly.
Add meat, crumbs, tomato juice, worcestershire, and soup mix.
Shape into loaf.
Bake in 350 degree oven 1 hour.
Cover until last 15 minutes of baking time.
Serves:

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the butter in casserole dish.
In mixing bowl, take softened cream cheese and mix with cream-style corn.
Add whole kernel corn, salt, peppers and garlic powder.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: debbie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl beat margarine or butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and baking soda.
Stir in chips.
Drop 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Cook at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: joann's pie
directions: Put coconut, pecans, and butter in baking pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand Milk,
add Cool Whip and 1 tsp vanilla.
Pour into pie shells, add coconut, pecans and caramel to top.
Put in freezer for 4 hours.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel
onions;
cut
in half crosswise.	Put in buttered casserole.	Mix
rest of ingredients; pour over onions.
Cover with foil.	Bake
at
350°	for 1 hour or until, beating occasionally.
Time of preparation: 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cholesterol-free banana bread
directions: About 2 hours before serving, or early in day, preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
With pastry blender, cut in corn-oil spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in bananas, undiluted apple juice concentrate, egg substitute, walnuts and vanilla just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into pan.

title: german meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 10 ingredients.
Shape into 18 meatballs.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown and remove meatballs.
Drain fat.
Spoon sauerkraut into skillet.
Top with meatballs.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Add water if needed.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put bread crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer vegetables to cover all over bread crumbs.
Pour soup, mixed with enough milk to make it pourable, over vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over the whole top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in a tight canister.
Use 2 teaspoons to each cup of boiling water.
Apple juice may be used instead of water.
Will keep for a long period if tightly sealed.

title: traditional rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter in a large bowl; add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, lemon peel, vanilla until blended well.
Beat in water, few drops at a time, only until dough starts to come away from sides.
Shape dough into large flat disc.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter; place on butter cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, mixed with flour.
Melt margarine in quart casserole.
Add milk, corn, salt, pepper and melted margarine to egg mixture.
Pour in casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk.
Hold finger over bottom of funnel; fill funnel with mix.
Drop into 1 inch of oil heated to 375°.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove and drain on paper towels, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: basque fish soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, wine, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
(At this point, may refrigerate or freeze.)
Add fish and simmer 7 to 10 minutes or until fish is opaque and flakes easily with fork.
Serve with crusty bread and salad.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and candies in boiling water.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt. Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: orange blossom muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add sifted biscuit mix.
Stir in marmalade and pecans.
Grease muffin pans; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Use small muffin tins.

title: lemon vegetable salad
directions: Stir jello and boiling water.
Cool until syrupy.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Place in 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Can be doubled in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oatmeal jello
directions: Follow directions on the box of oatmeal.
When it is done, take oatmeal off heat; add Jell-O (any flavor) and sugar to taste. Add fruit if you like.

title: orange pancakes
directions: Combine orange juice, milk, egg, salad oil and orange peel. Add pancake mix, stirring to remove most of the lumps.
Bake on greased hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles on surface break, flip only once.
Makes 12 to 14 (4-inch) pancakes.
Serve with Whipped Orange Butter or warm maple syrup.

title: pork pies
directions: Simmer pork, beef, water, onion, salt and pepper for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool; skim off fat.
Add enough bread to hold meat mixture together.
Add spices and applesauce; mix well.
Divide into 2 unbaked pie crusts; add top crusts.
Poke top and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
May freeze baked pies.
Wrap well.
Heat thoroughly before serving.

title: california salad
directions: Clean by washing escarole and romaine and sprigs of dill or coriander.
Tear and make large salad.
Add thinly sliced red onion.
Only add mandarin oranges, sunflower seeds and vinegar. Add oil just before serving.
It is a refreshing salad.
Enough for 8 people.

title: fried fresh corn
directions: Measure flour, wheat germ, baking soda and salt into large bowl; stir to blend.
In bowl of food processor, combine the eggs, bananas, honey, vegetable oil, lemon juice and vanilla until well blended.
Pour over flour mixture; add walnuts.
Stir with rubber spatula just until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until sides pull away from pan and pick inserted into center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes. Cool before removing from pan.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onion together with electric mixer until spreadable.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; chill until set.
Pour salsa on top.
Chop lettuce very fine and spread on top, then chop tomato into small pieces and spread on top.
Then sprinkle on cheese, then black olives. Chill.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chocolate covered frozen bananas
directions: You will also need 8 flat wooden sticks.

title: ham and cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Unroll crescent roll dough on an ungreased baking sheet. Pinch perforated edges together to make 1 solid sheet of dough. Spread mustard on dough. Arrange ham on mustard, then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bring long edges up over the filling and pinch ends to seal the center seam. Brush with beaten egg and top with sesame seeds and caraway seeds. Bake until bread is golden brown, 14 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack for 1 minute. Cut bread diagonally into 6 sandwiches or 12 appetizers to serve.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough in refrigerator overnight.
Melt margarine.
Add milk, cinnamon, brown sugar and pudding.
Heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Put pecans on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cut first loaf of bread into 1-inch pieces and put in pan (should be about 12 pieces).
Pour mixture over 1st loaf.
Then cut 2nd loaf and put over mixture. Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Immediately flip Sticky Buns out of pan onto aluminum foil.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add jellied cranberries and thawed strawberries.
Add cream cheese balls after jello is in mold.

title: cheese dates
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Cream margarine; add cheese.
Mix in flour, pepper and salt.
Stuff dates with pecans.
Pinch off small pieces of cheese mixture; roll around dates.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet-and-sour chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken wings.
Pat dry.
Cut off tips and discard.
Cut wings in half.
In a shallow dish, combine flour, lemon pepper and garlic salt.
Mix well and coat wing pieces.
Heat oil in skillet and brown wings on both sides.

title: pheasant stew
directions: Dredge pheasant pieces in flour mixture.
(Can also add a little thyme and ground bay leaf to this.)
Brown floured pieces in hot shortening in Dutch oven.
Add chicken broth, chervil, sage, parsley and garlic.
Simmer, covered, in Dutch oven for 40 minutes.
Add celery, onions, carrots and tomato sauce.
Simmer another 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms; simmer 15 minutes.
Can thicken "gravy" with flour paste if needed.
Serve with long grain and wild rice mixture (Uncle Ben's).

title: steak sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Microwave on high for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Heat cream until boiling in medium size pan.
Remove from heat and add German chocolate, chocolate chips and butter.
Stir until melted.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in liqueur.
Cover and chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in cocoa or powdered sugar or nuts.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain broccoli and place in buttered casserole. Mix mayonnaise, half and half, curry powder and cheese together.
Place chicken on top of broccoli and pour mixture over chicken and broccoli evenly.
Cover with bread crumbs, dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with rice, salad and rolls.
Yields 3 servings.

title: icebox bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt and set aside for 1 hour. Drain cucumbers and onions.
Mix together dry mustard, celery seed, sugar and white vinegar.
Pour liquid over cucumbers and mix together.
Put mixture in jars and refrigerate.
Let stand in refrigerator 1 day before using.

title: sour cream devil's food
directions: Cream the butter, gradually adding brown and granulated sugars.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Melt into the boiling water, cool slightly, then stir into the egg mixture. Add the combined soda and flour in about 3 parts alternately with the sour cream.
Add vanilla. Stir batter after each addition until it is well blended.
Bake in two greased 9-inch layer pans in moderate oven at 350° about 25 minutes.
Spread with chocolate frosting.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mel oleo in water until boiling gently.
Add flour and beat with wooden spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until smooth.
Spread in 15 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven (400°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Pour milk over bran flakes and set aside.
Beat egg, shortening and sugar together until smooth.
Stir in bran mixture and flour until "just moist".
Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, approximately.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate dipped peanut balls(unbaked)
directions: Cream the peanut butter with sugar.
Mix in walnuts and dates. Shape into small balls using level teaspoonfuls of mixture. Chill for several hours.
Keep chocolate over hot water while dipping peanut balls with spoon.
Coat 1 ball at a time.
Place on waxed paper lined tray and chill several hours or until chocolate is firm.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: dolphin chowder
directions: Saute fish in hot oil briefly.
Remove fish and set aside.
Add garlic and vegetables and saute lightly.
Add broth.
Stir in heavy cream and milk, oyster sauce and fish.
Heat through.
Thicken a little with gravy flour.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix children, dogs and cat together. Put them in the field, stirring constantly. Pour the brook over pebbles; sprinkle field with flowers. Spread under a deep blue sky and bake in a hot sun. When thoroughly browned, remove and set in bathtub to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring broccoli to boil.
Melt margarine.
Saute onions and celery.
Add flour.
Cook, stirring for 2 minutes. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Blend in soup.
Add broccoli and mushrooms. Bake in greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine egg and oil with milk; add to dry mix and mix well.
Insert wooden skewers into hot dogs. Cover hot dogs with mixture.
Fry in fat until golden brown. Serves 10 to 20.
