title: apple crunch
directions: Slice apples into baking dish.
Add sugar and spices.
Stir into apples.
Combine brown sugar, flour and butter and mix well. Mix 1/2 of this in apples and press down.
Put the other half on top of apples and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong pyrex dish, then mix sugar, flour, and milk together. Pour mixture over margarine and add fruit on top of this.

title: baked chicken
directions: Crush stuffing mix with a rolling pin.
Dip chicken in the chicken soup and roll in seasoned crumbs.
Cover pan with foil and spray.
Put chicken in a 350° oven and bake about 1 hour. Delicious.

title: bev's potato salad
directions: Wash and cook potatoes with skins in salted boiling water until tender.
Cool; remove skins and cube.
Sprinkle lemon juice over potatoes and mix gently.
Add all other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold together and then a little more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Put chicken in a container.
Pour Italian dressing over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Heat up the grill.
Cook chicken until done.

title: easy fresh peach cobbler
directions: Separate biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
In mixing bowl mix sugar and cinnamon.
Cover each piece with sugar and cinnamon.
Place on top of peaches.
Return to oven.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 2-quart casserole dish and layer as follows: Layer of potatoes, layer of Velveeta cubes, several pats of margarine, soup (mixed with milk), salt and pepper (go lightly on salt as Velveeta and soup have salt).
Repeat, making several layers of ingredients, and cover casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and uncover for the last 15 minutes.
Very good!

title: crock pot apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock pot. Cook on high with lid on for 4 hours, then remove lid and cook for another 4 hours. Stir occasionally; pour into jars and seal.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides in oil; season.
Grease casserole dish.
Place 1/2 of potatoes in dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of flour.
Add remaining potatoes and sprinkle with remaining flour.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Place chops on top; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook in slow oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: congo squares 2
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, eggs and flour.
Add vanilla flavoring and chips.
Bake at 275° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour in a glass baking dish.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Scoop out insides of potatoes.
Mix together mayo or sour cream, scallions, green pepper, pimento, cheese and crab; add to potato.
Put in shell under broiler; brown top.

title: corn scallop
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Bake in souffle dish or 11 x 7-inch baking dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Puffs up and gets a crusty top.
Serves 8.

title: good cupcakes
directions: Bring dates and water to a boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Cream oleo and sugar; add egg, cream of tartar and nuts.
Mix all ingredients together, except dates and water.
Last, add the dates and water and mix all well.
Bake at 325° to 350° in muffin tins. Can use paper cups.

title: em's sticky buns
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil and put in bottom of spring-form pan.

title: low country boil
directions: Fill large pot with water, add "crab boil".
Squeeze lemons and add lemon peels and salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
While waiting to boil, shuck and cut corn, and slice the sausage and onions.
Once water is boiling, add potatoes and sausage.
Cover and bring to boil again and cook 5 minutes.
Add corn and onions and cook another 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp but don't wait for the water to boil again.
Just cover for 5 minutes.
Drain and serve immediately.
Kitchen time 30 minutes and cooking time 15-20 minutes.
Serves 10-12 people.

title: mexican cinnamon cookies
directions: In a large bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, beat butter until light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, the flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, vanilla and salt just until combined.
Dough will be rather stiff.
Shape into a ball; wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: ma bell's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Use egg whites to make meringue.

title: evelyn's oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Stew raisins with enough water to make 5 tablespoons juice. Drain raisins and measure 5 tablespoons juice in container large enough to allow juice to foam up when soda is added.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles, then continue cooking for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Place egg yolks in a bowl.
Add half of hot mixture to egg yolks, then blend into remainder of hot mixture in saucepan. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, banana flavoring and vanilla.
Let cool.
Slice two bananas.
Arrange a layer of bananas in bottom of pastry shell. Pour the cooled filling over bananas; chill.
Before serving, whip cream until stiff; fold in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over top of pie.
Decorate with remaining banana.
Cut in slices and sprinkle with peanuts.
Makes 1 pie.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo (like pie dough).
Beat eggs well and mix into mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
May need to add more flour for soft dough to roll.
Roll thick for soft cookie; roll thin for crisp cookie.
Bake 12 minutes on 350° or until light brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Form into small quarter size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: magic cookie bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Yields 24 bars.

title: swedish almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening and butter with electric mixer until fluffy. Add powdered sugar and salt; mix well. Add next 4 ingredients, stirring well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Slightly flatten each dough ball. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: french canadian meat pie
directions: Combine pork, beef, onions and garlic in a large heated skillet.
Cook, stirring often, until meat loses its pinkness. Stir in seasonings and water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Uncover, simmer 10 more minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in potatoes.
Prepare pie crusts; spoon 1/2 of cooked meat into pie shell.
Fold edges over meat; brush with egg.
Roll out 10-inch round for top of pie.
Trim flush with edge of pan.
Brush top with egg.
Cut small slits in pastry near center.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Put apples in large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle with dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Dot with butter.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream eggs and 1 cup sugar.
Add 2/3 cup canned pumpkin, 3/4 cup flour and 1 teaspoon baking soda; beat.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan, then pour batter in and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Flip out of pan and roll in dish towel; let stand for 45 minutes.
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese, 4 tablespoons softened margarine, 1 cup powdered sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Add walnuts now if desired.
Unroll and spread with cream cheese mixture.
Roll into aluminum foil.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place slicing disc into a container. Cut cabbage on speed 5.
Empty into a large saucepan of salted water.
Cook over medium heat until tender; drain well.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Mix with enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Best if let set overnight.

title: pecan-coconut cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix with eggs and sour cream.
Spread 1/2 batter in pan.
Spread 1 box of dry coconut and pecan frosting mix.
Add remaining batter. Spread the other box of dry coconut and pecan frosting mix over batter.
Dot with stick of oleo.
Bake.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: *You may substitute 5 cups banana pulp for banana ice cream.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Each person builds his own serving in the order listed.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions.
Cool; cut into squares or crumble cake.
Line the bottom of a bowl with 1/2 of the cake.
Pour 1/2 of the Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Cover with 1/2 can of pie filling, then 1/2 of the vanilla pudding (made according to directions on box).
Cover pudding with 1/2 of crushed pineapple.
Top with 2 sliced bananas.
Repeat layers. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill 24 hours before serving.
Enjoy.

title: hidden treasure strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour half of mixture into an oiled 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Store remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature.

title: souper stew
directions: In large saucepan, add tomatoes, Italian seasoning, onion and garlic powders, and salt.
Boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and return to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until vegetables are almost tender, about 4 minutes. Stir in beans and pasta.
You can add some ham, turkey or beef for a whole meal.
Cover; cook until heated through.
Serve with Parmesan sprinkled on top.

title: muscadine jelly
directions: Measure exact amount of sugar and set aside.
Wash jars and lids with soapy water.
Pour boiling water into jars.
Drain well.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water. Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan, approximately 12 servings.

title: sundae brownie pie
directions: Bake crust at 375° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs; stir in sugar and butter.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add butter to mixture.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts; pour into crust. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until almost set (pie will not test done in center).
Serve warm or cool with ice cream.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and coarsely grind pears in food chopper.
Mix with rest of ingredients and boil for 30 to 45 minutes.
Place in sterilized containers.

title: sand tarts(cookies)
directions: Combine in order; heat.
Form in half moons.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: hot artichoke spinach dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and chop fine.
Thaw spinach, squeeze out liquids, chop up.
Mix artichokes, spinach and mayonnaise with the 3 cheeses and garlic.
When blended, put in greased 10-inch pie shell or shallow pan.
(Quiche pan works well.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Cook ground beef until browned (season as you like).
Layer ingredients in order listed in large casserole dish.
Melt cheese on top, if desired.
Serve with Doritos or Tostitos corn chips.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add Ricotta cheese, flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Spoon onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be frosted with your favorite frosting.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon.
Laying out each piece separately, place the chipped beef in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Put a chicken breast on top of each piece of chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; spoon on top of each chicken breast.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together and serve with sliced apples.

title: bruschetta
directions: Under a broiler toast both side of the bread.
Rub both sides of bread with a clove of garlic.
Drizzle with olive oil, top with the tomato slices, basil, pepper.
Serve warm.

title: grandma lydia's dumplings
directions: With pastry blender mix shortening, baking powder, salt and flour until crumbly.

title: smash cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until stiff with fork.
Dump on cookie sheet with an edge and smash to cover cookie sheet.
Mix next 4 ingredients for the topping.
Pour on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: martha's baked beans
directions: Peel onions and place in a 2-qt. casserole.
Combine all other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour in casserole over onions. Bake uncovered at 350° for about 2 hours.
Top with strips of crisp bacon if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add pumpkin, oil and water. Mix well.
Add all dry ingredients.
Bake in soup or vegetable cans at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 cans.

title: fatless fettucine(serves 2)
directions: Bring a 4-quart pot of water to boil. Cook fettucine according to package directions, about 10 minutes. Drain and keep warm.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix onion, cheese, water, cabbage, salt and pepper; cook to a boil about 3 minutes, then drain.
Make and mix ingredients with butter, flour, milk and chicken bouillon, then cook on stove until thick.
In a dish, layer the ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pudding dessert for diabetics
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
well.
Add the pure vanilla.
Layer whole graham cracker in bottom of an oblong dish. Top with the pudding mixture.
Layer whole graham crackers on top. (Space it so that a serving will not have but two graham cracker squares.)

title: old fashion mash potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Roll into oblong shape.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cut into slices and enjoy.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in pint jar, with lid, and shake jar vigorously.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: krispie crunch
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Butter dish and pour in ingredients.

title: my mother's crab imperial
directions: Combine crab meat, salt, red pepper, green pepper, 2 beaten eggs, 4 tablespoons mayonnaise and onion.
Mix well with spoon. Place in greased casserole and individual crab shells.
Mix remaining egg with 1 tablespoon mayonnaise.
Glaze crab meat mixture with egg and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat and slowly stir in the top of a double boiler.
Good on top of salmon, whitefish, meat loaf, etc.

title: date-nut cake
directions: Let
dates
stand in boiling water with the baking soda until cold.
Cream
sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add the rest of
the ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no-roll pastry
directions: In 8-inch pie plate, mix flour, sugar and salt.
Combine oil and milk in measuring cup; beat with a fork and pour all at once over flour mixture.
Mix with flour until flour is completely dampened.
Using fingers, press pastry evenly to pie plate on bottom and up sides.
Pinch edges lightly to flute.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Spread chicken in a casserole dish.
Mix together chicken soup, celery soup and Pet milk.
Spread over chicken.
Mix together cornbread mix, chicken broth and sage.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: sherry chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks until light, gradually add 1/2 cup sugar while still beating.
Add sherry.
Cook in top of double boiler over hot water, stirring constantly, until mixture is the consistency of soft custard.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in remaining sugar and salt.
Combine with the custard.
Spoon in pastry shell.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.

title: succotash
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, boil salted water; add beans and return to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Drain; scrape corn from cob and add with butter to pan.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cream and heat through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: mostaccioli(for a crowd)
directions: Saute chopped onion and green pepper.
Add the sausage, taking it out of the casing and simmer with the onion and green pepper. Add the sauces and let it simmer for about 20 minutes more.
Boil pasta in salted water until tender.
Drain the pasta.
Mix with sauce in a large pan.
Bake in oven at 350° until heated.
Enjoy!

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs yolks.
Dissolve baking soda in sour cream.
Add salt to flour.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to batter, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring; mix.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in stem pan at 300° until cake tests done (about 2 hours or longer).

title: spinach dip
directions: Yogurt Cheese: Place nonfat yogurt in coffee filter and place in strainer over a bowl.
Cover and let set in fridge overnight. Will be half the amount.
Use in place of sour cream.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Beat with hand mixer until sugar is dissolved.
Slowly add oil. Dressing will be thick and stay that way if oil is added slowly. Best when used on spinach and strawberry salad or red leaf lettuce with avocado and spears.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Squeeze juice from grated zucchini; drain well.
Break bread into smallish pieces and just moisten with milk.
Mix all ingredients and shape into cakes.
Roll in fine bread crumbs, if desired.
Fry in butter until lightly browned.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute onions and cabbage with margarine for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle flour over the mixture and stir. Add water, sugar, salt, pepper, lemon juice, caraway seed, bouillon cubes and tomatoes; mix all together.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with corn bread.

title: deluxe potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes 1/2 hour.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add potato chips on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: b~b~q spareribs
directions: Brown pork in a 325 oven for 1 hour, or cook on the grill until nicely browned on all sides.
In a large stock pot, saute onion and garlic in butter.
When translucent add all other ingredients. Bring to low simmer.
Add browned meat.
Cover and simmer on low for 3 hours.
Meat should be falling apart.
Serve over rice.

title: white trash
directions: Melt morsels and margarine together.
Add peanut butter and blend well.
Pour cereal into mixture and coat cereal well.
Put mix into small white trash bag and add powdered sugar.
Shake.

title: chicken and broccoli in white wine sauce
directions: Cut broccoli in bite
size pieces; steam and drain when done. Cook chicken cubes
in 1/2 stick margarine; then drain. In saucepan melt 1/2
stick margarine; add 3 tablespoons flour and stir until smooth over
low heat.
Add 1/2 cup hot chicken broth slowly, then add heavy cream and white wine.
Stir until smooth. Arrange chicken and
broccoli
in
baking
pan.
Pour sauce over and top with
cups
Parmesan
cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Pour
over
buttered spaghetti; toss and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water and debone.
Layer chicken with cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on top of mixture.
Slice oleo and put on top. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: mildred's daffie apple cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, vanilla, chopped apples, nuts or raisins and cinnamon.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in Bundt cake pan.

title: aunt freida's mulligan stew
directions: The key to this recipe is to put the ingredients through a food grinder.
Then cook until tender, stirring frequently to keep from sticking.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly coat a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with vegetable cooking spray. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt, ginger, allspice and pepper in medium bowl. Whisk pumpkin, sugar, eggs, milk and oil in bowl. Stir in dry ingredients just until blended. Fold in nuts. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: spanish rice with shrimp
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients, except shrimp. Mix well.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 10 minutes.
Reduce to Medium.
Microwave for 28 to 35 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir in shrimp.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake florida orange snowballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Form mixture into small balls. Roll balls in coconut or walnuts or both. Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix butter, sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: nutty no-bake cocoa balls
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cocoa in a mixing bowl.
Add condensed milk and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in chopped nuts.
Cover and chill until firm enough to handle (about 30 minutes).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional powdered sugar.
Cover tightly and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix well.
Freeze in Ziploc bags.
Take out at least 2 hours before serving.
Add 1 bottle ginger ale to each bag used.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda thoroughly, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cook onions, bell pepper and celery in chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix soup and broth with ingredients, chicken and spaghetti.
Place in dish and top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat and rice casserole
directions: Crumble ground meat in a buttered dish.
Sprinkle with rice and soup mixture.
Blend soup and water; pour over rice.
Cover with onions and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deep dish peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients except peaches.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add peaches in center. Do not stir.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: breakfast bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes, apples and raisins in a microwave-safe 2-cup bowl cooked with nonstick cooking spray.

title: apple cake
directions: Measure oil into large bowl; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add a little at a time to the creamy mixture.
Beat well.
Fold in apples and nuts. Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: cookie sheet chocolate cake
directions: In first bowl, add flour, sugar and salt. In 2nd bowl, eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. In saucepan, bring butter, water, shortening and cocoa to boil; pour into ingredients in first bowl. Mix well. Mix ingredients in 2nd bowl and add to other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 floured and greased pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, mix with sugar and let stand one hour. Drain and mix with grapes that have been halved, seeded and drained.
Cut marshmallows and nuts rather fine and blend all ingredients with whipped cream and chill.
Makes 15 or 16 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown pork; fry bacon and drain.
Press crescent dough on bottom and up sides of ungreased round pizza pan or 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan to form a crust; seal the perforations.
Spoon pork over crust.
Sprinkle hash browns, bacon, mushrooms and onions over pork.
Top with Velveeta cheese slices, then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Combine sugar, salt, soy sauce and vinegar; set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet; add red peppers and cook 5 seconds.
Add cabbage; cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir soy mixture and pour over cabbage.
Turn heat to high.
Stir until well mixed. Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: roast pork
directions: Combine
dry ingredients and rub into pork roast.
Bake in a 12-inch Dutch oven at 350° for 35 minutes per pound.

title: ziti broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients with ziti.
Add Viva Italian dressing.
Let marinate.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients; place in crock-pot and cook on low for 3 hours.

title: easy angel biscuits
directions: Mix well. Roll out and cut.
Place on greased baking sheet. Let rise about 30 minutes. Bake at 450° about 10 minutes or until browned.

title: baked carrots and apples
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients and put them into a lightly-oiled casserole dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Great with chicken.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending.
Fold together. Pour into shell.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together. Pour over meatballs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine in a heavy saucepan sugar, flour and butter.
Stir and cook until well blended.
Add milk.
Stir.
Beat 2 egg yolks until light.
Pour a little of the milk mixture over beaten egg yolks and then combine.
Stir constantly until thick.
Cool and flavor with the vanilla.
Pour into the baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue (out of the 2 egg whites).
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon cream cheese squares
directions: Unroll 1 tube of dough and place in lightly greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Seal seams and perforations. Set aside. In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread over dough. Unroll remaining tube of dough and place over cream cheese mixture, stretching to fit. Brush butter evenly over top. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Cool and cut into squares.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Bring beef bone, roast and 6 quarts water to boil.
Lower heat and simmer until meat is cooked, approximately 2 hours.
Remove scum.
Meat and soup bone can be removed from broth at this time. Drop potatoes into broth and immediately start making the dough.

title: dorothy's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and beaten egg.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, corn flakes, nut meats and vanilla.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a square baking dish or casserole dish. Sprinkle with Jiffy cornbread mix. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cornbread mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until set. Serves 4-6.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost berries.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and berries, beating until light.
Mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and salt.
Blend flour mixture into strawberry mixture just until flour is moistened.
Do not overmix.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Mix and cook until done.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on package.
When cake is done, cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, milk, vanilla and Cool Whip. Spread on cake.
Drizzle pie filling over icing.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, frozen, and stir until dissolved.
Let set until syrupy.
Add the pineapple, mashed bananas and nuts.
Pour half of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch flat dish and let set.
Spread with sour cream and carefully pour the other half of the strawberry mixture over this.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat lightly in oil.
Combine water, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, salt and 1 cup pineapple juice drained from chunks. Cook in saucepan until clear and slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over meat.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks and green pepper.
Cook 2 minutes longer.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat egg slightly; add flour, milk and rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. May put crushed potato chips on top.

title: ever-ready bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% bran cereal; set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in salt, soda, buttermilk and 100% bran mixture.
Add flour; mix well and add Bran Flakes.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
(Keeps 5 or 6 weeks.)

title: confetti rice salad
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Place broccoli in medium saucepan. Add 1-inch of water.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Rinse under cold running water to set color.
Drain well and set aside.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cottage and Mozzarella cheeses, and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles and drain.
In baking dish, put 1 layer noodles, 1 layer sauce, 1 layer cheese, 1 layer noodles, 1 layer sauce, 1 layer cottage cheese and 1 layer cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Cut all fruits fine.
Combine with nuts and mix thoroughly. Mix sugar and spices; toss with fruits until well coated.
Add orange juice and brandy; press firmly into buttered loaf pan. Cover with waxed paper.
Keep in cold place at least 10 days before serving.
Yield:
2 (8-inch) loaves.

title: garden slaw
directions: Toss onions, cabbage, celery, carrots and zucchini.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Toss with vegetables.
Refrigerate for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes 8 servings.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add milk, less 1/4 cup; bring to boiling point.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add flour.
Let rise 2 hours.
Add salt, soda, baking powder and as much flour as needed to make a soft dough (could use as much as 5 cups).
Store in refrigerator, covered.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: mom's old fashioned chocolate frosting
directions: Boil sugar, cream, cocoa and salt to soft ball stage.
Cool, then beat and add vanilla.

title: shredded beef
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 12 hours or less on high.
Serve with hard rolls.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Combine 1 cup milk and flour in small saucepan. Cook until paste and cool. Add sugar, oleo and peanut butter with electric mixer and beat and beat.
Add vanilla. Spread on cold cake.
This keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: kathy's dip
directions: You will also need a 13 x 9 baking dish or large round one.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan.
Add water to cover and 1 teaspoon of the salt.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat until water comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer about 20 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender; drain.
Place in large bowl.
Add milk, butter, pepper and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt; beat or mash until smooth.
Stir in 1 of the eggs and onion. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Divide mixture into 12 equal pieces.
With floured hands, shape each piece into a log.

title: snack bars
directions: Combine cake mix and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
If using a spice cake mix or carrot cake mix, sprinkle cookie bars with powdered sugar. Cream cheese icing makes other bars richer.

title: pineapple syrup
directions: Place pineapple (juice too)
and Karo syrup in blender. Blend for 10 seconds at high speed.
Delicious over ice cream, cakes, waffles and pancakes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in a double boiler or a bowl over hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: swedish jam cookies
directions: With mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and sugar in a large bowl until smooth.
Beat in corn syrup and egg yolks until well mixed.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Chill dough 20-25 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Dip into lightly beaten egg whites and roll in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
With thumb, make an indention in the center of each cookie.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 minutes, or until golden.
Remove from oven.
While still warm, fill with small amount of jam.
Cool on wire rack.

title: potpourri cookies(no bake)
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until well coated.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Cut a slit in 1 side of jalapenos and deseed them.
Stuff cheese into peppers.
Take 1 to 2 tablespoons of sausage and pat into a thin patty.
Press around jalapenos.
Coat them with Shake 'n' Bake.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix
eggs,
oil
and buttermilk.
Then add butter, cake mix and
pudding.
Beat well.
Bake in well greased Bundt pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spezzatao di pollo alla cacciatora(chicken red wine hunter's style)
directions: Wash and dry the chicken.
Heat the oil in a Dutch oven or deep skillet; brown the chicken in it.
Add the onions, green pepper, garlic, salt, pepper and oregano; cook for 10 minutes.

title: herb rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper. Saute about 15 minutes.
Add soups, water and rice.
Mix and pour in baking dish.
Top mixture with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Stir ingredients together in mixing bowl and bake in an ungreased pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy artichoke pasta sauce
directions: Drain artichokes and reserve 1/8 cup marinade.
Saute onion, garlic, basil, oregano and red pepper in hot oil over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add crushed peppercorns.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place half of mixture in a blender; blend until smooth.
Add remaining mixture.
Cover; chill 4 hours before serving.
Makes about 2 cups.
Good for dips, omelets, or just about anything.

title: beer and cheese fondue
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, add beer, heat and stir until thickened.
Turn off heat and add cheese.
Return to medium heat stirring constantly until all cheese is melted.
Turn heat to low and serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce in which the soda has been added.
All other ingredients may now be added.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for about 40 minutes.

title: cottage cheese lunch
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except toast.
Let mixture stand 2 hours so flavors blend.
Serve on toast; slice.

title: elaine hunt's roast dish
directions: Brown in iron skillet, then put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish lined with foil.
After you put in dish, sprinkle onion soup mix on top (1 envelope).
Put cream of mushroom soup on top (undiluted).
Cover with foil.
Cook about 3 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Clean fruit.
Cut up in cubes or bite sizes.
Combine in large bowl all the fruit and add yogurt.
It's refreshing.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Pour pineapple with juice into a large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Frost while cake is hot.

title: chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk. Set aside.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water.
Blend mushroom soup and chunks of Velveeta in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in drained broccoli and seasoned salt.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Boil potatoes until thoroughly done.
Drain and peel; mash until they are smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Shape into croquettes and roll in additional coarse corn flake crumbs.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Fry in hot fat.
Drain. Serves 8.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburg, green pepper, onion and celery together until brown; drain.
Mix pizza sauce, tomato sauce, oregano, garlic powder and salt and add to hamburg mixture.
Put noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the rest over noodles and mix together.
Put 8 ounce bag Mozzarella cheese over top and 4 ounce bag Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cheddar soup
directions: Cook breasts and chop into small pieces.
Reserve 2 cups broth and add salt, pepper, carrot, onions and celery.
Cook until tender (10 minutes).
Add milk; stir.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Serve.

title: cranberry drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugars together.
Beat in milk, orange juice and egg.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Blend well with sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Drop mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: country kitchen loaf
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cover and cook at medium heat until vegetables are tender, but not brown.
Combine cooked vegetable mixture with remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand or with a mixer until well blended.

title: mexicali egg casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat together eggs, milk, taco sauce, onion and salt until well blended, reserving a few pieces of chilies for garnish.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Garnish with reserved chilies.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Combine and let sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: For equivalent of 2 eggs, mix egg whites, dry milk and vegetable oil.
For flavor, add salt and for color, add yellow food coloring.

title: pannekuchen pancake
directions: Melt butter in a pie plate as oven preheat. Watch carefully so it doesn't burn. Mix flour, eggs and milk together with a fork in

a medium bowl. It's okay if it's a bit lumpy. Pour over butter in pie plate. Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minute or until golden brown and puffy. Take out of the oven and sift powdered sugar on top and serve immediately.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Steam zucchini for 5 minutes. Layer with cheese and onion in pie plate. Slightly beat eggs in cream, red pepper, salt and sugar.
Pour in pie shell and bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300°. Bake for 30 minutes longer or until firm. Before cutting, let stand 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Saute celery and onion in butter. Stir in rice and broccoli.
Add soup and cheese.
Spoon into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Add boiling water to potatoes, celery, onion, seasonings and bouillon.
Cover and cook until tender.
Blend flour with a small amount of the milk.
Stir into potatoes.
Add remaining milk and cook until thick.
Add Velveeta and Cheddar.
Stir until melted.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients, except oleo, and blend well.
Place in sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with oleo.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mark's cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt 1/2 cup Crisco in a 10-inch skillet. Combine all ingredients in a bowl, adding water until you get a creamy mixture.
Add melted Crisco.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Saute beef in oil until brown; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and 1 can of water.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Season to taste. Prepare a filling by mixing cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese and a dash of nutmeg.
Cook the lasagne noodles (enough for 3 layers in long dish); drain and wash.

title: quick tuna crisp
directions: Cook noodles
in
salted,
boiling
water until tender; drain. Stir in
tuna
and
oil,
pimento	and
mushroom soup. Reserve enough large
potato
for
top.
Crush remaining chips and cover bottom of
shallow	1 1/2 quart casserole.	Add tuna mixture.
Top with
whole potato chips.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) just long enough
to heat thoroughly, approximately 25 minutes and potato chips on top are crisp.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherry lover's surprise
directions: Mix instant pudding as per pudding instructions.
Add Cool whip, egg and sugar to half hardened pudding mixture.
Mix well and set aside for 5 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate sauce(for hot chocolate or for ice cream topping)
directions: Place in a saucepan sugar and add salt, cocoa and water.
Stir well, then cook over medium heat, stirring and watching constantly, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and refrigerate.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Mix ground beef mixture with other ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with cornbread mixture.
Bake until cornbread is done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Prepare box of wild rice as directed.
While this is cooking, brown hot sausage in skillet.
Drain off grease.
In same skillet, saute onion and water chestnuts (sliced thin).
Return browned sausage to large skillet and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and allow to simmer a short while.
Add prepared rice and mix well.
Put mixture into casserole and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon-wrapped shrimp
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap bacon around shrimp.
Secure with wooden picks.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour teriyaki sauce over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Makes 40 appetizers.

title: old fashioned oatmeal pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Cook beef, green and yellow peppers, onions and jalapeno pepper in skillet.
Drain.
In another pan, heat beans, chili powder, stewed tomatoes and salt.
Pour beans into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle meat mixture over beans.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until golden brown.

title: carrot bars
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the butter or margarine and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring to melt. Remove from heat.

title: salad
directions: Cut the lettuce, slice the cucumbers and carrots.
Add cheese and mix all of them with the salt.

title: electric lunch hot cakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: stuffed macaroni shells(with cheese stuffing)
directions: Cook shells as directed. Combine all cheeses, bread crumbs, salt, parsley and egg.
Fill parboiled shells immediately with cheese mixture.
In a baking pan pour half the spaghetti sauce. Arrange filled shells on top of the sauce in a single layer.
Top with the remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Add rest of ingredients, except noodles and crumbs; mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into casserole; cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until light and foamy in large bowl.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed (mixture will be stiff).
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then cut.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour filling into crust.
Refrigerate several hours.
Before serving, garnish with chocolate curls and chopped mixed nuts.

title: cheesy zucchini puff
directions: Steam zucchini until tender.
Mix in a large bowl the Cheddar cheese, tofu, eggs, salt, dill weed and croutons.
Add well drained zucchini and stir gently.
Turn into a shallow, oiled 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 3 as a main dish or 6 as a side dish.

title: whatchamacallit cake
directions: Mix the cake as directions say on back of box.
Bake it in long sheet pan.
After the cake is done, while still hot, take a fork and poke holes in the cake.
Pour the milk over the cake and let cool.
When cooled, take Cool Whip and spread on top of cake. Take chopped candy bar and spread over the top of Cool Whip.
Best if kept refrigerated.

title: aunt cleo's creamed corn
directions: Cut
corn
off cob and set aside.
In nonstick skillet, put your
bacon
drippings
and melt on medium heat.
Pour in corn, water,
sugar, salt and margarine.
Cook on medium heat until
the corn is bubbly and becomes thick.
It usually takes about 20 minutes to cook.
Mix flour or cornstarch in milk and add
to corn.
Cook again until thick and bubbly.
(Be sure to scrape the corn cob for creamy corn.)

title: golden chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm, if desired.
Cool; cut into bars about 2 x 1-inch.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and put in jar.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put butter, flour, egg, sweetened condensed milk, and sugar into a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat. Pour into baked pie shell.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip if desired.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Peel and cut in half lengthwise. Place on greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, turning potatoes once and basting frequently with syrup.

title: linda's potato soup
directions: Cook diced onion and cubed potatoes in chicken broth just until soft, not mushy.
You may want to use part chicken broth and part chicken bouillon with water.
Use at least 1 can of chicken broth.
Add margarine and milk to desired thickness, salt and pepper.
Cook until milk thickens.
Shredded carrots may be added, if desired.
May add Velveeta or Cheez Whiz, if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook and debone chicken; chop fine.
Add some chopped onions, chopped sweet pickles and boiled eggs.
Add enough salad dressing to make it hold together.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain all juice from fruit and cut into small pieces.
In a large bowl, combine all fruit, lemon juice and pecans.
Mix well. Add condensed milk.
Gradually add Cool Whip, while stirring. Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, water and salt until tender, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and raisins.
Beat eggs just until blended.
Add gradually, while stirring briskly, to rice, milk mixture.
Return to low heat and cook, stirring constantly until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: low-fat fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with wax paper; set aside.
In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in milk and sugar; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove pan from heat; gradually stir in chocolate chips.
Add prunes, marshmallow cream, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into pan and chill.
Cut into 48 pieces when firm.

title: jiffy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and butter in water until potatoes are soft and very tender.
Add milk, parsley and seasonings.
Heat until almost boiling.
Top with grated cheese.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Boil chicken; set aside.
In saucepan, saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add chicken soup and milk.
Simmer until heated through.
Add pimento and chicken.
Pour over rice or egg noodles.

title: vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: *You may use chopped cauliflower, broccoli, mushrooms, tomatoes and radishes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion and drain.
Spread hash browns in 9 x 13-inch dish, spread sausage and onion mixture over top.
Spread mushrooms on top.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over all.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is good to make the night before, just pop in oven in the morning.

title: herbed potatoes(makes 8 servings)
directions: Place potatoes in large pot and cover with cold water.
Boil until almost tender, about 30 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes crosswise into 1/2-inch thick rounds.
Whisk remaining ingredients in large bowl to blend.
Add potatoes and toss thoroughly to coat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
Prepare barbecue (medium heat).
Remove potatoes from marinade and place on grill; reserve marinade.
Cook potatoes until golden brown, turning occasionally, about 12 minutes. Transfer to platter.
Brush remaining marinade over and serve.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Separate 2 eggs and use whites for meringue.
Beat eggs well. Mix all and pour into a 9-inch pie shell, unbaked.
Put in cold oven.
Turn oven to 225° and bake 30 minutes.
Turn up to 250° and finish baking.
Put meringue on and brown.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix together.
Place in casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin tins with Pam or line with paper cups.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with blueberries.
Set aside. Mix liquid and dry ingredients separately; then combine, mixing just enough to moisten.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill each muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes.
Makes 10 - 12 muffins.

title: heather's quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Slowly warm cream cheese and stir in salsa and chicken.
Wrap in warm tortillas and serve with lettuce, onion, tomatoes, etc.

title: granola bars
directions: Beat 2 eggs.
Add melted or room-softened butter, honey and vanilla.
Add dry to wet ingredients stirring only until well blended.
Add chocolate chips, raisins and nuts. Chopped dates may be used instead of raisins.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 25-30 minutes. Cut into bars while warm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Grease and flour two bread pans and pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with wooden spoon.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Use fork to flatten. Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
These burn easy so cook on top rack.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Beginning with flour, add milk and flour alternately and end with milk, beating after each addition.
Blend in vanilla. Pour batter into three generously greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool layers before removing (about 15 to 20 minutes).
After removing layers, slice each layer in half to make a six layer cake.

title: peach pie
directions: Arrange peaches in unbaked pie shell.
Mix together all remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except crushed walnuts.
Form into a ball. Roll in crushed walnuts.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening; add dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup milk and bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk, eggs and
vanilla. Beat another 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: texas swiss steak
directions: Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Dip in flour, salt, pepper and mustard, mixed together.
Brown pieces in hot oil.
Place in casserole.
Scatter cut up vegetables on top of meat.
Pour sauce of ketchup and brown sugar over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: grape delight
directions: Wash and drain grapes.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Add grapes and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8.

title: cake icing
directions: Mix the first 4 (or 5 if chocolate) ingredients together at medium speed.
Add the confectioners sugar and water.
Add sugar first, then pour water over sugar.
Beat thoroughly.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and melted margarine.
Press into bottom of oblong pan or 2 square pans.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Layer cream cheese mixture, bananas and pineapple. Put whipped cream on top.
Cut cherries in half put on top of whipped cream.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oh boy casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet with oil.
Add soups diluted with water as instructed on can, soy sauce and rice; mix well. Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Put 3/4 can of chow mein noodles in a casserole.
Add above mixture, then put rest of noodles on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix at low speed until dough forms. Shape dough into balls using rounded teaspoonful of dough.
Roll balls in additional sugar.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and top with candy Kisses, pressing down until cookie cracks around edge.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into 3/4-inch balls.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool and roll in sugar a second time.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain well.
Mix cucumber, bell pepper, tomato, onion and salad dressing (as much as you like). Add spaghetti.
Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over oats in large bowl.
Stir well and cool.
Crumble yeast into bowl; add 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 cup warm water and 1/2 cup flour.
Stir until smooth and let stand 10 minutes, then add to first mixture with remaining sugar, flour, salt and shortening.
Shape into ball and place in greased bowl. Brush top with salad oil.
Cover with clean towel and let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) for 2 1/2 hours, or until double in bulk, then knead down.
Shape into loaves and place in 2 greased/oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Brush top with salad oil.
Cover again with towel and let rise for 2 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes two loaves.

title: barbecued beef short ribs
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add onion and saute until tender. Add flour, stirring well.
Gradually add cider.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in relish, catsup, basil, allspice and cloves.
Cut ribs into serving size pieces and grill over slow coals for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Brush ribs with sauce.
Cook additional 20 minutes, basting and turning frequently.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: busy day dinner
directions: Place meat in crock-pot early in the morning before leaving for work or starting your busy day.
Add golden mushroom soup and mix.
Do not add any water.
Set crock-pot on medium and let it do your work.
The meat will add liquid to the soup for a nice gravy.

title: sugar free fruit smoothie
directions: Place fruit in blender, blend till smooth. If using fresh strawberries, drop ice in one at a time while blender is running. Blend until ice is crushed. May need to add more orange juice to thin down smoothie a little. You can also add 1-2 fresh peaches, peeled and cut up. Makes 1-2 smoothies.

title: alan's chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Boil chicken until fully cooked.
Place on barbecue grill, baste with remaining sauce, cook until golden brown.
Then eat until your heart's content.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook garlic in oil.
Cook garlic, ground beef, salt and pepper in a large saucepan until meat is done.
Add Ragu sauce; cook about 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in salt water until tender; drain. Cover baking dish with noodles, add meat sauce, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Beat first three ingredients using slow speed on mixer.
Fold in pudding mix.
Reserve 1/2 cup cherry pie filling.
Marble remainder into cheese mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with remaining cherry filling.
Chill well and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In medium mixing bowl, blend cream cheese with salad dressing, chili sauce, lemon and onion juices and Worcestershire sauce. Rinse and drain shrimp. Combine with cheese mixture. Serve as dip for crackers. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: breast of chicken casserole
directions: Mix sherry with 1/2 cup water.
Add soups.
Add raw rice.
Mix all of these together really well.

title: quick pickled beans
directions: Bring beans and juice to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Put in covered container and refrigerate 2 or 3 days.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut each bun lengthwise into fourths.
Makes 4 sticks.
Melt butter, cheese and garlic powder together.
Brush mixture lightly on cut sides of buns.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until toasted.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings; 119 calories per serving.
Two sticks per serving.

title: tuna-apple salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with mayonnaise, soy sauce or whatever dressing you like.

title: holiday breads(many variations!)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 inch loaf pan. Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl at low speed.
Beat on medium for 30 seconds, scraping the bowl often.
Bake 60-65 minutes or until bread tests done.
Refrigerate overnight for better slicing.

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Grease large 10-inch spring-form pan.
Make graham cracker crust and press into bottom of pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese; add cream cheese and beat on high until creamy.
Blend in sugar and eggs. Add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add margarine and sour cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Let cake stay in oven for 2 hours or longer.
Do not open oven door!!!!

title: soft old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Then add oatmeal, sugars, shortening, eggs, milk, vanilla and raisins. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese fish bake
directions: Arrange fish fillets in a single layer in a greased 10 x 6 x 2 inch shallow baking dish.
Stir cream of mushroom soup and pour over fish.
Season with pepper, and then sprinkle with shredded cheese and paprika for extra color and flavor.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with 2 cups grated Cheddar cheese and bake until melted.

title: boeuf bourguignonne (beef burgundy)
directions: Cut sirloin into 1-inch cubes.
Bring to room temperature. Melt butter in skillet and brown meat on all sides.
Add the rest of ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for one hour, covered.
For the last 15 minutes, uncover and stir several times.
If juice is too thin, increase heat so that excess moisture will evaporate.
Remove bay leaf.
Spoon over noodles or rice. Very good with wild rice.

title: shoo-pic patties
directions: To every cup of fish, add 1 cup of boiled potatoes and 1 egg. Smash boiled potatoes (let cool).

title: crispy chocolate bars
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in a large saucepan; stir over low heat until smooth.
Add corn flakes; stir until well coated.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes before cutting into bars.
Bars are easily removed from pan.
Yields 32 (1 x 2-inch) bars.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter until fluffy and beat in sugar.
Add egg; beat again. Add milk and beat.
Add vanilla and beat.
Mix dry items together in a bowl and add them to other mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, until dough is firm.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine meat, onion, eggs and bread to form 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Make sauce from remaining ingredients.
Simmer in sauce for 1 hour.
Serve from chafing dish.
Yields 36.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; flake.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Form into 4 or 5 patties.
Pan-fry in small amount of vegetable oil until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together and spoon into casserole dish (buttered).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 350° (nuts optional).

title: baked beans and hamburger
directions: Brown in skillet the ground beef, onion and bacon; drain. Partially drain beans. Add ketchup, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar. Combine meat and all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: atlanta banana bread
directions: Mix baking soda and sour cream, set aside.
(It will bubble.) Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour, bananas, vanilla and salt.
Fold in sour cream mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in ovenproof dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dairy queen ice cream
directions: Bring milk almost to a boil, then soften gelatine in water (2 tablespoons water to 1 package gelatine). Add this to the hot milk. Also add sugar to hot milk and salt. Cool, then add cream and vanilla. For 1 1/2-gallon freezer.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep in airtight container.
To serve, put desired amount in cup and fill with boiling water.

title: bacon hot dog snacks
directions: Cut hot dogs into 4 pieces. Cut bacon strips into 3 pieces. Wrap hot dog pieces with one bacon piece.
Pack tightly in ovenproof dish.
Cover wrapped hot dogs with brown sugar (about 1/2-inch of brown sugar).
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: tortellini bean soup
directions: In a large pan or Dutch oven, saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and pepper 3 minutes. Add vegetable broth and basil. Bring to a boil. Stir in tortellini and zucchini.
Simmer, uncovered, 8 minutes (for fresh) to 15 minutes (for frozen) until tortellini is tender. Stir in beans and heat through.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: golf balls
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, coconut, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Melt margarine; pour over and mix.
Add more butter, if needed, until all is wet.
Make into balls.

title: orange cake
directions: Blend together at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
When reasonably cool, prick the cake with a fork.

title: frozen peach cream pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then pureed peaches and lemon juice. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour equal portions into crust.
Freeze for 4 hours or until firm.
Remove 5 minutes before ready to serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and let simmer a few hours.

title: quiche
directions: Prebake pie shells until very lightly brown.
Crumble cooked bacon in bottom of pie; layer cheese over bacon.
Beat eggs, spices, cream, half and half and onion with mixer 2 to
3 minutes. Pour over bacon and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Check closely during last 10 minutes.
Done when inserted knife comes out clean.
Do not overcook.
Makes 1 pie; double recipe makes 3.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together 3 minutes over low heat.
Add marshmallows and partially congeal.
Add Pet milk or whipping cream; add nuts.
Chill until firm.
(If using Pet milk, chill before whipping.)

title: jello fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese, drained fruit and nuts.
Sprinkle dry jello over the mix and fold in until completely colored.
Place into serving dishes and refrigerate covered to chill.
This has very little sugar content.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Drain berries well; mix Jell-O and cake mix.
Add oil, water and eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each; last, fold in berries. Bake in two 8-inch pans which have been greased and lightly floured at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna cheeseburgers
directions: About 15 minutes before serving, preheat broiler.
In medium bowl, flake tuna; stir in celery, mayonnaise, lemon juice, milk and salt.
Spoon mixture on top of 3 bun halves.
Place cheese slices on remaining halves.
Place all bun halves on rack in broiler pan.
Broil just until cheese melts, about 3 minutes. Makes 3 sandwiches.

title: bierocks
directions: Cook meat until browned, then add cabbage and onions.
Cook until cabbage and onions are tender, then cool.
Make yeast dough as you do for bread.
Roll and cut in about 6 inches square. Take a number 12 ice cream dipper or 2 tablespoons of hamburger. Put in each square of dough, then fold dough over meat and fasten it closed.
Let rise and bake in a 350°
oven until lightly browned.

title: pork dijon
directions: Trim pork; slice into 2-inch wide pieces.
Flatten with a mallet.
Coat pork with mix of flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine.
Add cider vinegar to pan dregs; cook down.
Add cream; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add mustard and remaining 1 tablespoon margarine.
Cook 2 minutes.

title: breakfast knots
directions: Boiling water bath method:

title: carrot bake
directions: Layer cooked carrots in 9 x 13-inch pan until pan is half full.
Layer onion, Cheddar cheese and celery soup.
Put stuffing mix on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: turkey supreme
directions: Mix together the macaroni, milk, butter, soup, onion, salt and pepper.
Let stand overnight or all day.
When ready to bake, add turkey and cheese.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jello fluff salad
directions: Add hot water to Jell-O; add juice and cold water.
Set Jell-O.
Fold oranges and whipped cream in Jell-O.
Serve in glass bowl.

title: lo-mi-ro
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese) in bowl.
Pour into large casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spanish fried chicken
directions: Clean and skin (if desired) chicken.
Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Place all chicken pieces in bowl at once and coat.
Pour combined liquids into bowl.
Thoroughly mix all by hand.
Refrigerate for 1/2 to 1 hour, then fry in pan using the oil.

title: angel treat
directions: In large bowl cream powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Gently fold in the whipped cream.
Slice cake and tear into bite-sized pieces.
Gently mix together and place in covered serving pan and refrigerate.
Top with cherry pie filling at serving time.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and onion soup mix in a bowl.
Pour over chicken breast.
Lay a pineapple on each breast.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered.

title: chili
directions: Brown the chuck and onion in oil or "brown" in microwave.
Add the beans, tomato, chili powder and salt to above.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 1 to 2 hours.
Or cook on top of stove for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: lumber jack bean bake
directions: Fry
bacon
crisp; drain.
In the usual amount of bacon drippings
or
margarine,
add onion and sweet pepper and cook until
tender.
Add
bacon and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar, vinegar,
mustard, garlic salt and salt and simmer 15 minutes. In a large casserole (4 quart), combine the 4 types of beans; toss lightly
to mix.
Spoon bacon mixture over top of beans. Bake, uncovered,
in
preheated
oven
at
for 50 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour hot water over dates; let stand.
Add butter to hot mixture.
Cream sugar, egg and vanilla together; add dates and nutmeats to mixture.
Last, add flour, salt, soda and baking powder, all sifted together.
Mix and bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.
Bake in well-greased baking pans or cans.
Fill cans only halfway full.

title: broccoli bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp; set aside. Beat eggs with cream and cheese.
Stir in broccoli, salt, garlic powder and lemon pepper.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Mix everything, except for 1/2 can onions.
Bake in casserole dish 45 minutes at 350°, covered.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti giovanni
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter (oleo) and then add mushrooms.
Add tomatoes (chopped), crabmeat, sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Add spaghetti.
Pour this mixture into a large greased casserole and top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: marinated italian chicken
directions: Take 1 cup of friendship and add 2 cups of thoughtfulness. Cream smoothly with a pinch of gentleness and a dash of powdered kindness.
Beat together with a spoon of hope, one heaping pint of work, 2 level teaspoons of temperance, a sprinkle of humility and 1 teaspoon of problems for strength.
Mix slowly in a bowl of loyalty with 1 cup of faith, 2 cups of good sense and several drops of right feeling.
Blend all these ingredients gently together with love and simmer until all of the hate and prejudice is cooked away.
To congeal, add 3 heaping spoonfuls of laughter, 1 of play and a sprinkle of praise.
Season with melted gratitude and stir constantly with enthusiasm.
For extra taste, moisten with sympathy and, for the best results, bake in a good-natured pan.
This will last a long time and gets better with age...but serve often.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Tear chicken into bits and place on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over.
Top with 1/2 package stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Chop nuts and cherries and mix with milk.
Add crushed wafers (save enough crushed wafers to roll mixture).
Make two long rolls and roll in wafers and powdered sugar.
Chill and slice.

title: oriental roast
directions: Place heavy duty aluminum foil in a shallow pan.
Center roast on foil.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over roast.
Turn roast to coat.
Seal foil airtight and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover top with cheese slices. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and cheese is melted in good.

title: hot crab philly spread
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Spoon into ovenproof dish. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup toasted almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or party rye bread.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in unbaked pie crust at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. To test for doneness, insert knife in center of pie. If it comes out clean, the pie is done.

title: rolo-chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; blend well.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Chill dough.
For each cookie, shape dough around 1 Rolo candy, covering completely.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Cut chicken in pieces, remove skin and fat.
Boil in seasoned water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth to cool; debone and cut into chunks.

title: prune spiced nut loaf cake
directions: Cut prunes from the pits into small pieces.
Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in well beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture, alternately with coffee.
Blend in prunes and nuts.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook fresh blueberries with 1 cup sugar and cornstarch. Add enough water to dissolve sugar while cooking, about 1/3 to 1/2 cup.
Cook on low heat
until
mixture
is thick and blueberries are done.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.	Mix well
and
pour in pie shells.
Then pour blueberry filling over
that.
Garnish
with
Cool	Whip. Refrigerate until good and cold.
Slice and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix together, save 1/4 cup cheese and put in casserole dish. Cook 30 minutes and take out of oven.
Spread 1 cup sour cream (8 ounces) on top.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup grated cheese. Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients. Mix all together.
Cook until tender.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: boiled shrimp in beer
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp; and cover.
Return to boil and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir, then let stand covered off the heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove shrimp from liquid.
Cool promptly with cold running water.
Drain and chill.
(Leave shell on.)
Sprinkle with cocktail sauce and let everyone peel and eat.

title: chewy bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry-pineapple colada
directions: In a blender or food processor process in batches, 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into pitcher and refrigerate.
Stir before serving over ice in tall glasses.
Makes 8 cups.

title: french-style peas
directions: Fry bacon crisp and remove from fat.
Dice onion and garlic bulb and saute.
Pour peas and liquid in can into onion and garlic.
Add 1/4 cup water and cook on medium heat until liquid has almost cooked out.
Crumble bacon and add to bowl before serving (bacon stays crispier that way).

title: sun dill pickles
directions: Place in 1 gallon jar in order listed.
Fill jar to about 2-inches from top with pickles.
Fill jar with cold water.
Add a little more dill (1 to 2 flowers).
Add 3 cloves of garlic, 3 grape leaves and 2 slices of white bread.
Place lid on tightly.
Let stand in sun for 3 to 4 days.
Throw away top bread and grape leaves.
Keep pickles in fridge.

title: italian sausage roast
directions: Cut sausage into serving pieces and put in a roasting pan. Brown at 350° in the oven, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
If there are excessive drippings, drain some of them off.
Add potatoes, green peppers, onions and spices to taste.
Mix together and bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms and bake for another 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes; dip in beaten egg and then in cracker meal to which salt and pepper have been added.
Cook in hot fat until golden brown on both sides, turning once.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil. Stir in flour; stir rapidly over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs all at once. Continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cup, 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Shape into fingers 4 1/2 x 1 1/2 inches.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Fill and frost.

title: broccoli raab vinaigrette
directions: Trim the tough stems from the broccoli and discard.
Cook the broccoli raab in a large pot of boiling salted water until tender, 10 to 13 minutes.
Drain well.
In a small jar, combine the vinegar, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and shake until the salt dissolves.
Add the oil and shake again to combine.
Toss the broccoli, chopped red onion and red-wine vinaigrette together. Serve at room temperature.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pickled rolls(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Drain pickles.
Place two slices thin meat overlapping. Spread with cream cheese and top with pickle.
Roll up, chill, then slice.

title: angel food torte(low-fat)
directions: Combine milk, pudding and pineapple. Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers. Spread bottom layer with 1 1/3 cup pineapple mixture.
Repeat. Spread remaining on top.
Sprinkle top with coconut and garnish with cherries. Refrigerate.

title: "sweet-tart" dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Serve over green salads.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown the sausage.
Combine remaining ingredients with sausage and microwave for 15 minutes at full power.

title: cheese tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add hamburger and cook until brown and crumbly.
Drain. Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: lime mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Pour into blender.
Add cream cheese or Ricotta cheese.
Blend.
Drain pineapple into measure cup, add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to mixture and blend for a few seconds.
Pour into bowl.
When almost jelled, mix in crushed pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Heat raisins and water in pan.	Boil slowly to plump up raisins.
