Add sugar and raisins; boil slowly about 15 minutes. Mix cornstarch with small amount of water and add along with a touch of	butter	or
margarine if desired.
Let cook another minute or two.
We always serve this with ham.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Add dry ingredients (no need to sift); blend well.
Stir in shredded zucchini (dates and nuts).
Bake at 325° in greased angel food, Bundt or 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick comes clean.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt butter; blend to flour for thickness.
Add 2 cups of milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and onion powder. Stir in cheese, then add to potatoes.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Add oatmeal.
Flatten balls of dough and bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Fry beef until browned.
Chop onion and garlic; add to beef after grease has been poured off.
Add tomatoes and spaghetti. Cook slowly until thick.

title: apricot nut loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix thoroughly sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk, orange juice and rind.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in.
Blend in apricots and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake about 70 minutes at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine 1 cup butter, 3 teaspoons vanilla, 1/4 cup cocoa, 1 cup nuts and next 3 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Pour into large greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Melt marshmallows and spread over cake. Combine remaining 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup nuts, 1/2 cup cocoa and milk in saucepan until melted.
Add remaining vanilla, mixing well.
Frost cake.
Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: school days casserole
directions: Cook
hamburger
and onions together until done.
Drain off grease. Add tomatoes and beef stew seasoning mix.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Put
in	baking	dish
and
top	with grated cheese. Bake in 375°
oven	until
cheese is melted, approximately 20 minutes.

title: lena's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add extracts.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with the milk.
Bake in prepared pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes in preheated 325° oven.

title: steak elegant
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil, using high heat.
Add onions.
Saute until tender-crisp.
Add soup, sherry, mushrooms and garlic salt.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender (or cover and bake at 350°).
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and sugar together.
With a pastry blender, cut shortening into flour mixture; add buttermilk.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to flour mixture; mix well.
Add extra flour, if needed.
On a floured surface, roll dough out to desired thickness; cut with biscuit cutter and place in baking pan.
If desired, let rise in warm place for 10 minutes, or bake immediately in a 450° oven for about 10 minutes or until done.
The unbaked dough can be stored in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
electric
mixer,
beat
cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla
until light and fluffy.
Place 1 cookie in each of 18 foil
baking cups on cookie sheet.
Pour cream cheese mixture into cups, filling about 1/2 way.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.	Cool
thoroughly.
Top with desired fruit (*canned cherry, blueberry,
pineapple
or strawberry pie filling).
Refrigerate.
Makes 18 individual cupcakes.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix
all
the ingredients together, adding the crabmeat last. Spread
on
muffin halves.
Cut each half into quarters and
may be
placed
in
freezer bags and frozen, if desired. When ready to
use,
lay out on cookie sheet and bake in oven until bubbly.

title: southern banana soup
directions: Combine milk, dates, ginger, cardamon and nutmeg in blender. Puree until smooth (medium speed).
Add bananas.
Blend well until smooth and creamy.
Stir in yogurt.
Pour into a bowl.
Cover and chill thoroughly before serving.
Serve garnished with pecans. Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, egg, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: frozen peaches
directions: In large container, mix orange juice and sugar until well blended.
Peel and slice peaches into mixture, stirring occasionally to coat slices well.
Fill freezer bags and freeze.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; use 1 cup boiling water to dissolve jello. Add liquid, salt and sugar.
Stir to dissolve.
Refrigerate.
When set, add fruit.
Top with Cranberry Fruit Salad Dressing.

title: microwave bitter orange chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients in microwave dish.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice and stir to smooth paste.
Gradually add remaining orange juice, stirring constantly until smooth.

title: russian salad
directions: Combine jello with 3 cups of hot water.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add 2 cups of cold water.
Add cream cheese and stir until all the cheese has dissolved.
Then mix in the pineapple and marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator to jell.
Using instructions on package of Dream Whip, do as directed.
Top jello mixture, sprinkle with nuts.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix melted oleo, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Add 1 cup of hot water; cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of water.
Add this and beaten egg to other mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Make out as you want.
Keep the rest in refrigerator.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, Crisco, powdered sugar, sugar and vanilla. Add flour and nuts. Roll into 1-inch balls and cook at 350° for 10 minutes. When done, roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: quick and tasty hors d'oeuvres
directions: In an 8 or 9-inch skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add Raisin Bran.
Over low heat, stir slowly and constantly until all the Raisin Bran is well coated (approximately 1 minute).
Remove from heat.

title: nana's bread
directions: Mix and knead.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Divide into 4 loaves and let rise until 2/3 size of finished loaves.
Bake at 350° as rising completes and loaves are brown on bottom as well as top, for 1/2 hour or 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix the pudding and milk together.
Pour over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Mix together the glaze and strawberries and put on top.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill before serving.

title: bran health muffins
directions: Mix together in mixing bowl the bran flour or oat bran cereal, wheat flour, baking soda, salt, cloves and cinnamon.
Blend dry ingredients together and add egg, vegetable oil, honey, molasses, yogurt and fruit juice or water.
Mix until well blended.
Fill well-greased muffin pans 3/4 full and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 muffins.

title: raisin raggedy anne
directions: Drop by small spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: brenda foreman's chip dip
directions: Heat all together slowly.
Eat with tortilla chips.
Can or freeze.
Also good for stuffed potatoes.

title: harlequin beans
directions: Brown bacon; add garlic and onions just before bacon is brown and crisp.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and mustard.
Cook for 10 minutes on burner, stirring often.

title: pleasing pea salad
directions: Put peas in medium bowl.
Top with cheese, pickles and onions.
Add mayonnaise; mix.
Sprinkle eggs over top.
Chill and serve.
Serves 4.

title: slightly different meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, water and poppy seed.
Let stand 10 minutes, then add oil and eggs that have been beaten together. Put all together and beat about 4 minutes on medium speed.
Put into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cover meat, green peppers and onion with water.
Cook until almost dry.
Add catsup, pepper seeds and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer 30 minutes.
If too thick, add a little water.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Boil sausages and drain.
Over medium heat in a heavy saucepan add brown sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar and La Choy sweet and sour sauce.
Bring to boil.
When mixture boils reduce heat and add 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Stir until thickened.
It may take a little more cornstarch.
Add 4 to 6 drops of red food coloring.
Add sausages and serve hot.

title: sun-kissed carrots
directions: Peel and dice carrots.
Place in saucepan.
Sprinkle with onion, salt, pepper and brown sugar substitute.
Pour in diet pineapple-orange.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: better than heaven cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box. Cool for 15 minutes. Poke holes in the top of the cake every 1/2 inch with the handle of a wooden spoon. Drizzle with condensed milk and let stand for 5 minutes. Drizzle with caramel/fudge sauce. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Spread cake top with whipped topping and sprinkle with toffee chips.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Toss cooked vegetables into cooked rice and parsley.
Blend soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream in small saucepan over low heat.
Blend soup mixture into vegetable mixture.
Add chicken.
Bake in oiled 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° until bubbly and browned.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix and pour into crusts.
Refrigerator for 1 hour to set.

title: festive corn 'n broccoli dish
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Cover; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until crisp-tender, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas and cheeses in double boiler on warm burner; don't boil.
Heat tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil.
Put about 2 tablespoons of cheese in each tortilla and 1 rounded teaspoon of soup mix.
Roll and place in pans. Use remaining soup mix to put over tortillas and top with cheeses. Cover with foil and cook 20 minutes in a 350° oven; remove foil and cook 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
May add oregano, if desired.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Cream the butter thoroughly, adding sugar gradually until blended.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add extract.
Continue beating at moderate speed, adding flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 75 to 90 minutes at 325°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble
sausage;
brown
and drain.
In bowl mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread cubes and stir.
Add cheese and sausage and mix.
Put in glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place in	refrigerator
overnight.
Bake	45 minutes or until done at 350°.
Cool a few minutes before slicing for serving.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix everything together and pour it (thick) into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix all ingredients.
Stir to blend. Using a medium size spoon, spoon batter into a hot skillet with deep fat.
Cook until brown.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Mix first three ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bacon.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour can of cherries in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar over the top of cherries.
Sprinkle the cake mix over that. Melt the margarine and pour over everything.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: *Any fruit, fresh, frozen or canned, can be used in this recipe.

title: spareribs and mild barbecue sauce
directions: In large glass bowl, microwave to heat and blend.
Mix ingredients and pour over spareribs.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake another 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Pare and core pears.
Mix with sugar and nuts.
Let stand for 1 hour, stir often as mixture makes its own juice.
Add dry ingredients to pears.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Do not use beater, stir by hand.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook thoroughly chicken and dice.
Place the chicken and vegetables in baking pan.
Next pour soup over it and top with pre-made stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Five to 8 minutes before it is done, top with cheese slices.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix well; roll into logs.
Roll in chili powder (optional).

title: quick cherry balls candy
directions: Drain cherries; set aside.
Beat ingredients (not the graham crackers) until well blended.
Wrap a teaspoonful of batter around each cherry, covering completely.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs. Chill for 1 hour.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Add baby food and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to first mixture. Add nuts.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes.
Bars are moist.

title: cream cheese pies
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Fold into crusts. Top with pie filling. Extra Cool Whip can be used to top off the pie filling.

title: chicken crunch oriental
directions: Cook chicken. Remove skin and debone.
Cut into dice like pieces.
Combine all ingredients with 1 cup Chinese noodles.
Put into 2-quart or oblong baking dish.
Spread remaining 1/2 cup noodles on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yields 5 servings.

title: marshmallow - peanut butter candy
directions: Bring butter, sugar and cream to a boil.
Boil 5 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and nuts.
Beat until smooth and pour into buttered pan.

title: meringues
directions: Beat egg whites foamy; add baking powder and salt.
Beat stiff.
Add vanilla, then vinegar, then water.
Beat.
Add sugar, beating until mixture holds stiff.
Press meringue through pastry tube, forming ring on greased baking sheet.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 1 hour.

title: walnut cheese ball
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Beat together with mixer until well blended.
Chill.
Then form into balls or rolls as desired.
Roll in toasted nuts.
Wrap well in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator until about 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: burger beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in skillet.
Add ground beef until brown.
Add barbecue sauce and beans; mix and simmer for 10 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or slow cook in crock-pot if taking to a party.
Great served with baked potato and tossed salad.

title: granny kirkpatrick's raisin tarts
directions: Prepare your favorite pie crust recipe and line 12 muffin tins.
Set aside.
Slightly beat the eggs with a fork.
Add butter, brown sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat again.
Pour into pie-crust-lined muffin tins.
Place raisins in each tin.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Form in a loaf pan.
Cover with ketchup.
Bake for 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: snow dusted trees
directions: In a nonstick pan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add broccoli and saute until tender.
Stir in pepper, then sprinkle with lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Dust with cheese before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thaw Cool Whip.
Thoroughly drain oranges and fruit cocktail. Stir dry jello into Cool Whip. Add oranges, fruit cocktail and chopped nuts.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: taco rice
directions: Brown burger.
Blend in canned tomatoes.
Add water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Mix burger, rice and taco seasoning together. Cook 20 minutes.
Add shredded lettuce, cheese and tomato on top.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla, then add the water, cocoa and oleo.
Bake this at 350° for 20 minutes.
While the cake is in oven, make the icing.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients except noodles and cheeses.
Simmer at least one hour.
Add ricotta or cottage cheese.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In large casserole dish, layer noodles, meat sauce, and half of mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let sit for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: wheat germ zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugars and flavoring.
Continue beating until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine flour, wheat germ, soda, salt, baking powder and walnuts.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture until just blended.
Divide into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch or 3 (7 x 3-inch) pans.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Cool 10 minutes in pans, then remove and cool thoroughly on racks. Freezes well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add sour milk and mix.
Add flour and baking soda; mix.
Add bananas and walnuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for about 1 hour.
Make sure toothpick inserted in middle of loaf comes out clean.
Mushy banana bread is not good!

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together; place in casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese, almonds and noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: After mashing potatoes, add other ingredients.
Form into patties.
Place on well sprayed baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 40 minutes, turning once.
Pancakes should form a brown crust. Serve with fresh parsley and tomatoes.
A compliment to scrambled tofu.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and celery. Add remaining ingredient and mix well. Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes until good and hot. Add grated cheese to top during last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil, add jello and stir until dissolved. Add other ingredients except Cool Whip.
Let cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli spears on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, cutting large spears in half lengthwise.
Place large slices of cooked chicken in single layer over the broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and pour over the first 2 layers. Sprinkle cheese on top of this.
Combine melted butter and cornflake crumbs and sprinkle over layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries and sweeten; allow strawberries to set and make juice.
Drain juice and measure in heavy pan.
For each 1 cup of juice use 2 level tablespoonfuls cornstarch.
Mix cornstarch and equal amount sugar.
Sift into juice, stirring well.
Bring to full boil.
Remove from heat and add berries, cool.
Dump into baked pie shell, top with Cool Whip.
This also makes a good icing for yellow cake topped with Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Cut in the shortening with pastry blender.
Stir in milk with fork until dough follows fork.
Roll out onto floured board.
Roll into a rectangle.
Spread with melted butter and top with sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Roll up the long way and slice.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Batter: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove and let cool.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the sour cream, fruit cocktail and Mandarin oranges; mix well.
Add coconut and marshmallows. Fold together and chill for at least 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pie shell for 10 minutes, then remove from the oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt chips with butter.
In large mixer bowl, beat chocolate mixture with remaining ingredients, except the nuts, until smooth.
Add nuts; pour into pastry shell; bake 35 to 40 minutes or until the center is set.
Refrigerate.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sift flour before measuring. In a bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Stir in sugar, salt and margarine. Add egg, mix in flour until dough is easy to handle. Place in greased bowl

turning greased side up. Cover with plastic wrap. Let rise until double in bulk. Make out rolls. Place in greased pan. Cover and let rise till double in bulk. Brush with melted margarine. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 12-15 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert cake
directions: Pour cake mix into bowl. Remove 1 cup and set aside. To remaining mix, add egg and oleo. Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.

title: beef shish kabobs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Add beef cubes. Cover and refrigerate at least four hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Season chops with garlic salt, thyme and oregano.
Place in shallow dish.
Mix onion, pepper and mushrooms in tomatoes and pour over pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with rice.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In skillet, brown meat; pour off fat.
Add chilies and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Cool.
In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside.

title: loas kind of eggs
directions: Crack eggs into a bowl.
Put in soy bean sauce, monosodium glutamate, fish sauce and black pepper; stir.
Put oil in a pan. When oil is popping, pour in eggs and fry until golden brown.

title: cherry-apple lattice tart
directions: Prepare crust according to package directions.
Roll out on lightly floured surface to 11-inch circle.
Fit dough into a 9-inch tart pan with removable bottom, pressing gently but firmly against bottom and sides. Roll rolling pin over top of pan to trim off excess dough.
Place pan in freezer 10 minutes.

title: lazy woman's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Place in a large casserole dish. Cover with chopped onion.
Add a layer of Tater Tots.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 450° for approximately 45 minutes, or until bubbly.
Cover with grated cheese and put back into oven until melted.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Fry unbreaded wings in frypan.
Melt margarine and stir in remaining ingredients.
Coat cooked wings with sauce and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pepper rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and sour cream; put into casserole.
Top with chilies and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly, covered.

title: flop cake
directions: Beat together.	Put
into 9-inch pan (square or round). On top,
add
brown sugar, cinnamon and little lumps of butter or margarine.	Bake
at 325° for 30 minutes.
You can also add peaches or apples, cut up.

title: spoon-up eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt until very thick and lemon colored; stir in rum.
Fold egg yolk mixture into whipped cream.
Fold egg whites into egg yolk mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve in cups with spoons.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yields 12 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: patty's cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges, undrained, with a mixer.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan until it tests done.
Cool.
Thicken crushed pineapple with cornstarch. Spread on cake.
Slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Mix the pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Beat together softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix pudding and cream cheese mixture together. Spread on top of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: zucchini spice muffins
directions: Beat egg; blend in brown sugar, oil and vanilla until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; stir until moistened.
Spoon batter into paper-lined microwave muffin cups, filling cups 2/3 full. Microwave (High) 6 muffins at a time, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until no longer dough, rotating pan once.
Repeat with remaining batter, microwaving 4 muffins 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: china fried rice
directions: Saute rice in a little peanut oil for a few minutes.
Add rice to water and cook as on package.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in pan over medium heat and add eggs.
Stir quickly with fork until thoroughly cooked.
Transfer to small bowl and chop into small pieces.
Over medium heat (can use same pan, just wipe), add onions and ham. Stir quickly 2 to 3 minutes until golden or your preference.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Blend quickly.
Add eggs.
Toss and serve. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Combine all together and mix well.
Pour into cookie sheet that has been lined and greased with wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Roll up on a tea towel.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread with filling and roll up, carefully removing wax paper.

title: italian horn cookies
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour, shortening and salt.
Mix in sugar, lemon juice and nuts.
Add milk until mixture is pasty.
Pinch off pieces of dough.
Roll dough into a round. Place a small amount of sugar mixture on dough.
Roll dough and bend into crescent shape.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press the bread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place cooked sausage or bacon on top of the bread.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Lightly beat eggs with milk; pour over the top of the ingredients in the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: mama's snow cream
directions: Combine snow and cream in bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator or serve immediately.

title: chicken mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle and bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat to just simmering.
Cook until chicken is very tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken and place on a cookie sheet to cool.
Strain broth and cool; then refrigerate until fat is hardened.
Discard fat if desired. Debone chicken and discard bones and skin.
Package about 2 cups of chicken per container;
package broth separately, about 2 cups per container.
Be sure to label carefully.
May be used for noodles, dumplings, chicken pie, chicken salad, chicken enchiladas, etc. Makes about 6 pints of chicken and 6 pints of broth.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat. Cook noodles.
Drain.
Combine egg, cheese, Parmesan cheese and meat.

In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan, layer half each of the noodles, meat, Mozzarella and spaghetti sauce. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in mixing bowl, including yeast. Add Crisco.
Mix well.
Add warm water.
Mix well (about 10 minutes).
Let rise until double.
Dump on floured board and mash down.
Shape into small loaves or rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: momma's blender popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place ingredients in blender in order listed.
Blend thoroughly, about 20 seconds.
Bake in hot, greased muffin pan at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Allow to chill for several hours before serving.
Serve with chips, tacos, and other Mexican dishes.

title: french tomato salad
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Slice them thinly or cut into wedges.
Place them in a bowl.
Combine the rest of the ingredients; mix thoroughly and pour over tomatoes.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Add sugar, eggs, salt, butter, milk, butter flavor and raisins to boiled and mashed sweet potatoes.
Pour into greased pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, meal, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Add eggs and sweet milk to mixture.
Bake in well-greased pan at 450° until brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening until crumbly like coarse meal. Add egg, water and vinegar. Mix well and form into 3 balls. Chill in the refrigerator. Makes 3 crusts. May be frozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour, oatmeal (processed), salt, baking powder and soda. Mix all ingredients well and then add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts (if used).
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: italian chicken soup with meatballs
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in large pot and cook for 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken pieces in Pyrex dish.
Mix Minute rice with all 3 soups.
Pour over chicken.
Bake about 1 hour in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: household cleaner
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in squirt bottle and use to clean your "dirt".

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts. Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grapefruit jelly
directions: Measure juice in large pan (not aluminum).
Mix in pectin and bring to a boil.
Stir in sugar all at once.
Bring to rolling boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Skim and pour into sterilized jelly glasses.
Seal.

title: spinach squares
directions: Thaw and drain chopped spinach. Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut in small 1-inch squares.

title: egg beaters
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in covered container in refrigerator for up to 1 week.
Freezes well.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix with 3/4 cup sugar and place in unbaked pie shell.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cover with top crust and crimp edges firmly.
Make several slits in top to allow steam to escape. Brush top with milk.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Bake 10 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 350° and cook 50 minutes more.
Serve hot with Vermont cheese.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: lemon cheesecake pie(no bake, easy)
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine evaporated milk and pudding mix; beat 2 minutes. Set aside. In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until light. Gradually add lemonade concentrate; continue beating until smooth, light and fluffy, 3 or 4 minutes. Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixtures blending thoroughly. Pour filling into pie crust. Chill at least 3 or 4 hours or over night before serving.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan and dust with cocoa.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as per directions.
Pour in large cake pan and bake.
Cool.
Cook eggs, sugar, flour, milk and butter over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add well drained pineapple and spread over cooled cake.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle this generously with coconut.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.
Always keep refrigerated.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in oleo.
Add rest of ingredients to mixture.
Stir well and pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and cook at 350° until it bubbles. This casserole may be prepared the day before and baked when needed.
Serves 8.

title: homemade graham nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add the buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour out onto an oiled 12 x 16-inch flat pan and spread evenly with a spatula.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until the batter is firm, medium brown in color and shrinks from the sides of the pan.
With a metal spatula, completely loosen the hot patty from the pan.
Allow to cool on a rack for several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Break the patty into chunks and put through a meat grinder, using a coarse blade or pulse in a food processor until coarse crumbs are formed.
Divide crumbs between two 12 x 16-inch pans.
Bake for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Let cool, then store in an airtight container.
Serve as a cold cereal.

title: chocolate chip cookie pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In small mixer bowl, cream butter; add eggs and vanilla or bourbon. Combine sugar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts; pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.
Cool about 1 hour; serve warm. Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green jello salad
directions: Chop pecans and set aside.
Drain pineapple; keep the juice.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put into a greased and floured pie dish.
Bake at 375° approximately 1 hour.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Blend melted butter with sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Add eggs; beat with spoon, well.
Mix all together.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of a 9-inch cake pan with waxed
paper.
Spray pan and paper with vegetable oil spray.
Dust pan with flour.

title: chocolate stack cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Mix ingredients well and pour into pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar and let stand.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add juice and chill until partly set.
Add pineapple, nuts and celery.
Pour in mold and chill until set.

title: quick garlic onion ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine onions, butter and garlic in a small bowl, set aside.
Separate dough into individual biscuits. Gently pull apart each biscuit to separate into two halves, making 20 pieces.
Brush one side of each piece with garlic-onion mixture.
Arrange pieces, onion side up, and overlapping, in a 9-inch circle on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 1 ring.

title: main dish casserole
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain grease off.
Mix the two soups, milk, green chilies and enchilada sauce.
Place Doritos on bottom of casserole dish.
Place mixture on top.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Cook until cheese bubbles.

title: artichoke pizza appetizer
directions: On ungreased jelly roll pan, lay out the rolls, pinching together to make a large rectangle.
Bake 10 minutes in a 400° oven until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Mix artichoke hearts, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, salad mix, mayonnaise and Parmesan in bowl. Spread onto crust.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Cut into squares.

title: ketchup
directions: Place the tomatoes and onions in a large heavy saucepan; set over moderate heat and cook, covered, stirring often until soft, 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove vegetables, then put them through a food mill and back into saucepan, discarding any solids.
Stir in brown sugar, garlic, bay leaf, celery seed, allspice, cinnamon, cloves and vinegar.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Adjust heat so the mixture bubbles gently.
Simmer, uncovered, until it has the consistency of ketchup.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator. Makes 2 quarts.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cakes in 1/3 cup water to which 1 tablespoon sugar has been added.
Put the shortening in hot milk and allow to cool.
Then add the dissolved yeast and egg (not necessary to beat egg).
Blend in the 2 cups flour and beat well.
Then add the other cup of flour and the salt, blending well, and then allow to stand 20 minutes.
Knead lightly for 3 to 5 minutes on floured board, using as little flour as possible.
Cover with cloth and allow to stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in well greased roll pan and brush lightly with melted butter.
Allow to stand until doubled in size. Bake in moderate oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
(Rolls can be served in 1 1/2 hours.)

title: fish in wine sauce
directions: Place fillets in a single layer in baking dish.
Arrange sliced tomatoes over top of fillets.
Blend flour into butter in saucepan.
Add milk gradually and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in wine and basil.
Pour sauce over top of tomatoes and fish and add crumbs.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: bacon squares
directions: Mix mayo, Worcestershire sauce, salad seasoning and paprika. Stir in cheese, bacon, peanuts and onions.
Spread about 3 tablespoons mixture on slices of bread.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 10 minutes.
Cut each slice into 4 pieces while hot. Serve at once.
Makes 56 pieces.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Cook meat in a heavy skillet over medium heat, breaking into small pieces.
Drain; add garlic, onion and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except buns.
Simmer until thick, about 20 minutes.
Spoon onto toasted hamburger buns.

title: small chocolate cake(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt butter or margarine in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Beat in egg. Gradually add flour, coffee, cocoa and baking powder.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread batter into pan and bake 30 minutes.

title: pasta puttanesca
directions: Bring 4 quarts water to a boil in a large pot.
Add salt and stir in the spaghetti.
Cook until tender, but still firm.
Drain immediately when done and transfer to 4 heated plates.
While spaghetti is cooking, drain the tomatoes; cut them crosswise into halves and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Combine tomatoes and olive oil in a skillet and bring to a boil.
Keep the sauce at a full boil and add remaining ingredients except pasta, one at a time, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat slightly and continue to cook for a few minutes, or until sauce has thickened to your liking.
Serve immediately over hot pasta and garnish with additional chopped parsley.
Makes 4 main course portions.

title: pumpkin curry soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over med-high heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook stirring frequently, for 2 - 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in curry powder, salt and pepper, cook for 1 minute. Add broth and pumpkin, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cook for 15 - 20 minutes (stir occasionally) stir in milk, transfer mixture to blender or food processor.
Cover, blend til smooth. Serve warm.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon hearts and water until hearts dissolve. Stir occasionally.
Put cloves in some slices of apples and add to syrup.
Cook slowly until apples are tender, about 5 minutes.

title: tofu and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut pork into thin slices.
Combine remaining 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce, ginger, garlic and sugar in small bowl; stir in pork.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in hot pan.
Add pork and stir-fry 3 minutes; remove.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in same pan.
Add onion; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add napa; stir-fry.
Add tomatoes, pork and soy sauce mixture.
Cook and stir gently until sauce boils and thickens.
Gently fold in tofu; heat through.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Mix in flour, stirring only until blended.
Add coconut, if desired. (Batter will be thick.)
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.
Cool and cut in bars.

title: white wine with sun-dried tomatoes and garlic sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add wine and tomatoes.
Stir 2 minutes.
Add cream and boil until mixture is reduced to sauce consistency, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and garlic.
Whisk until just melted.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over, our favorite, grilled tuna steaks or scallops or whatever you wish!
Makes enough sauce for 2 servings.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients. May use juice from chilies mix and add to dry ingredients just until moistened.
Add eggs, milk and oil.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water; mix 1/4 cup of the bouillon and the remaining ingredients except potatoes, cheese and mushrooms. Pat in 9-inch skillet to within 1-inch of edge. Pour remaining bouillon around edge. Place potato wedges on meat loaf in spoke fashion. Cover and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender, 30 to 40 minutes. Arrange cheese on potatoes; sprinkle with mushrooms. Cover and cook until cheese is melted, 2 to 3 minutes. Garnish with parsley, if desired. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hawaiian icebox cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl; beat at low speed of electric mixer 30 seconds.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
(Check at 25 minutes.)
Let cake cool in pan on wire rack.
Combine milk and pudding mix in a medium bowl; beat at low speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until thickened.
Cover and chill 5 minutes. Stir in pineapple.
Pierce 48 holes in top of cake, using the handle of wooden spoon.
Spread pudding mixture over cake.
Next, spread whipped topping over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle topping with shredded toasted coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 16 servings.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Mix in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add baking powder, flour and milk (alternate between each).
Beat well after each.
Add vanilla. Blend all together.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate cookie cake
directions: Combine water, margarine, shortening and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil.
In another container, mix together eggs, sour milk, vanilla and soda.
In large mixing bowl put flour, sugar and salt.
Pour melted mixture over dry and mix well.
Mix in egg mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (large jelly roll pan is good).

title: "grama" scott's coffee cake(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, nutmeg, sugar, 3/4 cup oil and cinnamon.
Take out 1 cup for topping.
Add a bit more oil to remainder (1 tablespoon).
Add baking powder, salt and egg.
To 1 cup sour milk, add baking soda and pinch of salt.
Pour milk over mixture and stir.
Do not remove lumps.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle the cup of topping over cake batter. Cover with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and salt. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rocky road ice cream
directions: In heavy saucepan heat milk until it scalds.
Mix sugar, eggs, cornstarch, salt and cocoa and stir into milk.
Cook until it forms a soft custard.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup cold milk and stir into custard while the custard is lukewarm.
Add miniature marshmallows and let dissolve slightly.
Let mixture cool, then add vanilla and almond extracts, evaporated milk, whipping cream and light cream.
Add chopped candy bar, chopped almonds and chopped cherries.
For added flavor, ripen in freezer at least 2 hours before serving.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, mix with sugar and refrigerate overnight. Next morning, add bananas, marshmallows, grapes and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Whip cream.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Fold into cranberry mixture.
Refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Add taco mix.
Roll up in white tortillas with cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour soups and milk over enchilada casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use 1/3 pecans in cheese ball.
Save 2/3 pecans to roll ball in.
Mix ingredients; chill overnight.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in real lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into shell and chill until set.
Top with strawberries and glaze.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 300° until custard is set.

title: super s'mores
directions: Place 1 graham cracker square on paper napkin to keep cracker crisp.
Top with chocolate and marshmallow.
Microwave at High until marshmallow puffs (15 to 20 seconds).
Top with other cracker square.
Let stand one minute.
For all kiddies - 1 serving.

title: finger paints
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium low heat, combine the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir well and add the cold water.
Stir constantly until well blended and the mixture begins to thicken, about 15 minutes.
Divide the mixture into 4 to 5 plastic containers such as margarine tubs.
Add food coloring to make the desired colors and add a couple of drops of Ivory liquid soap to make cleanup easier.
Be sure to spread newspaper over the work area and dress appropriately.
Create masterpieces on fingerpaint paper, butcher paper or waxed paper.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Pour into raw pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin supreme pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, salt and Blair vanilla.
In the empty pumpkin can, mix the eggs and flour with eggbeater until flour is mixed well.
Sprinkle Blair cinnamon into mixture.
Stir until evenly distributed.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 50 to 60 minutes until inserted knife comes out clean.
Makes 4 pies.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple and juice in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Stir once or twice.
Melt butter and crackers and put over top of pineapple mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crumble cookies in bottom of pan.
Spoon soft ice cream over cookies.
Pour syrup over ice cream (use amount you want).
Spoon Cool Whip over chocolate syrup.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion in oleo.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, water, rice, cheese and cooked onion in a bowl.
Add broccoli.
Put in 8 x 10-inch glass casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine the oats and boiling water; let stand for five minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Have ready a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the oatmeal mixture.
Blend well and turn into the prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in a greased casserole pan. Sprinkle the layer with 1/3 of the flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Repeat, making 3 layers. Pour until just barely covered, the milk preferably hot.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: peachy orange yogurt whip
directions: In a blender container, combine yogurt, juice, milk and Equal. With the blender running, add peaches a few at a time through opening in lid.
Blend until smooth, then add ice cubes one at a time through the lid.
Blend until slushy.
Makes 4 (7 ounce) servings.
Diabetic Food Exchanges, 1/2 milk and 1 fruit.

title: russian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Coat with apricot preserves and Russian dressing.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Pour water into dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and place pineapple slices on chicken.
Finish baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften; add onions, ham and m.s.g.
Chill and serve.
This recipe will serve 3 people.

title: candy rams
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter, egg and vanilla.
Put in greased casserole.
Blend brown sugar and flour. Stir in 1/2 cup melted butter and nuts; pour evenly over sweet potato mixture.
Cook at 375° for thirty minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until dissolved.
Set in refrigerator until thick. Add 1/2 pint Cool Whip.
Put in an 8 1/3 x 13-inch pan.
Decorate with maraschino cherries (cut in half) or top with pecans, if desired.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf or serve as a light dessert.

title: hillbilly beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Mix and add rest of ingredients.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Brown and place in casserole dish. Cover with rice.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over pork chops and rice.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in 7x11 container, mix broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.
Spread over cornbread.
Spread onions then tomatoes, top with Miracle Whip and then bacon bits.
Place in refrigerator.
When ready to serve spoon out amount you want and mix.
Rest will keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: tuna-potato bake
directions: Arrange in layers beginning with potatoes in a 2-quart baking dish:
potatoes, tuna, onion and cheese; repeat until all are used.
Pour soup over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. May be topped with bread crumbs.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Sift flour and add to mixture.
Add milk, vanilla and salt.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: sherried beef
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine meat, soup, sherry and soup mix in a large casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Great over rice or for stew; add vegetables during the 3rd hour and increase temperature to 350°.

title: beef pot roast with vegetables
directions: In large pan on stove top, add 1/4 cup cooking oil.
Dredge roast with flour, salt and pepper, coating both sides.
Brown in pot, both sides, on medium heat.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Add enough water as meat cooks to keep covered.
When meat is tender, add potatoes and carrots.
Cook 20 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat in a large skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add beef and cook until brown.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Heat 5 minutes or until warm.
Serve over hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over sliced cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Set in refrigerator for 2 hours. Put in containers and freeze.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix the above ingredients and chill.
You may add cottage cheese to taste.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Layer crackers close together on cookie sheet. Heat butter and sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle chips evenly over saltines.
Place cookie sheet in oven that is turned off.
Spread chocolate chips (after they soften) over the crackers using knife.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate and chips in large bowl. Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Fold in chips and grated chocolate.
Pour into greased and floured bundt or tube cake pan.

title: chickpea dip
directions: Boil chickpeas in juice for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Drain. Place chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic and salt in blender. Blend for 15 seconds to make an almost smooth, thick paste.
Place dip in a plate and garnish with parsley, radishes, red peppers and pickles.
Cover dish with olive oil.
Enjoy with pita bread.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and arrange pineapple, cherries and walnuts over the margarine.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 45 to 55 minutes.
Immediately invert pan on heatproof serving plate.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin pie topping
directions: Cream together.
Pour over top of pumpkin pie ready to be baked.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: snicker squares
directions: Melt butter and caramels over medium-low heat.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add peanuts and mix well.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 32 squares.

title: sherried beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours. Serve with rice, Chinese noodles or egg noodles.
Makes 10 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Measure flour, salt and baking powder and sift together.
Melt shortening and chocolate over heat.
Gradually add sugar to egg mixture and blend.
Add chocolate mixture to egg and sugar mixture. Stir.
Mix in flour, then add nuts and vanilla.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: artichoke heart and spinach casserole
directions: While onions saute in butter, line bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish with artichoke hearts, quartered.
Divide ingredients and cover artichokes with two layers of onions, Cheddar cheese, spinach, lemon juice and pepper.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Cover and heat thoroughly in 350° oven about 1/2 hour.

title: bill's dijon tenderloin
directions: Heat skillet and melt butter. Saute shallots. Add white wine; simmer until wine is reduced 1/2 way. Add the cream, mustard and Mojo; simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Pour sauce over meat and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Grill tenderloin 5 minutes on each side or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.
The last 10 minutes take out and put cheese on top.

title: green tomato nut bread(in honor of "jimmy creed")
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Combine eggs, sugars, oil, lemon juice and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat well. Stir in the green tomatoes.
Add dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool in the greased and floured loaf pan for 10 minutes after it is done.
Remove to wire rack and finish cooling.

title: spicy sausage and lentil stew
directions: In a large pan, combine lentils, 5 cups of water and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.
In skillet, cook sausage and onion until meat is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through, then add all of this to cooked lentils.
Simmer, covered, for at least 15 minutes.
Will be thick.
Great with cornbread.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts.
Beat 4 minutes. Bake in cake pan.
Sprinkle on top mixture of sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Spoon Hot Butter Glaze over hot cake.

title: anna's salad
directions: Drain can of carrots and peas.
Cook bacon and then crumble. Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift, measure flour and resift with baking powder, salt, nutmeg, soda and sugar.
Break eggs into mixture.
Add syrup and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix as little as possible to form dough (until all ingredients are moistened).
Turn into a well-greased loaf pan.
Top with thin apple wedges, dipped in margarine, then in sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour. Cover pan for the first 20 minutes of baking.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Form in two loaves and bake 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy fudge
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
May be kept in refrigerator.

title: apple appetizers
directions: Peel apples.
Cut into bite-size chunks.
Place in a large bowl. Add jello powder; toss gently until apples are coated. Place into clean serving bowl.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Cook together in either pressure cooker or on top of stove in a big boiling pot until ham is done.
Serve hot.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix all together; place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemonade and cold water.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale to punch bowl.

title: succotash
directions: Cook ground chuck and drain.
Add gumbo mix, sliced smoked sausage, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine carrots, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar and spices.
Stir in eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter in three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.
Frost layers with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: tola's refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Melt over low heat Pet milk and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and add cracker crumbs, cherries, pecans and raisins.
Mix all together and press into greased loaf pans.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese with sugar; add eggs and blend.
Add vanilla and whip until smooth.
Place a vanilla wafer cookie in the bottom of each cupcake baking liner.
Fill each cup 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
When cool, top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Makes 18 to 20 tarts.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Take a large quantity of cheerfulness and let it simmer without stopping.
Put with it a brimming basin full of kindness. Then add to it a full measure of thoughts for other people.
Mix into these a heaping teaspoonful of sympathy.
Flavor with essence of charity.
Stir well together and then carefully strain off any grains of selfishness. Let the dish be served with a sauce of love and the fruit of the spirit.

title: fried oysters
directions: Dip each oyster in egg, then flour and in egg again.
Finally dip in bread crumbs.
Coat oyster completely in each step of the process.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and coconut alternately.
Lastly, add flour.
Bake in paper cups for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread one half of the chilies on the bottom.
Combine last five ingredients together. Cover chilies with one half of the cheese and one half of egg mixture, repeat.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bleu burgers
directions: Form meat into 8 thin 1/4 pound patties.
Form 4 thin smaller patties of Bleu cheese.
Place the Bleu cheese patties in the center of 4 of the hamburger patties.
Top with the other 4 hamburger patties and press firmly.
Press around the edges to seal.
Broil or grill to desired doneness.
Serve on toasted buns with desired garnish.
Makes 4 Bleu Burgers.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread candy quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool. Cut in squares.
Yields 2.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Cut scallops into halves.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Crush package of crackers; mix with 1/4 cup butter, melted.
Mix in with scallops.
Place all in casserole; top with bread crumbs, butter slices, lemon pepper and parsley. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes enough for 4 servings with a salad.

title: biscotti(italian cookies)
directions: In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Gradually add flour (mixture will become sticky).
Make small balls or other shapes from mixture.
Place on a slightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: very moist chocolate cake(good)
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add boiling water last.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: thelma's apple butter
directions: *Cut and core apples; cut into small pieces.
Cook and put through food mill.
Measure out 10 cups cooked apples (like applesauce).

title: allison's breakfast idea
directions: Spread soft butter on bread.
Place Cheerios on butter.
Eat.

title: cattail dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix.
Place in casserole and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Knead down into a ball.
Grease casserole dish well.
Place ball of dough in casserole.
Let rise until double in bulk and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Coat well one 12 x 17 baking pan with Pam.
In heavy 5-quart saucepan with lid (tight-fitting), combine sugar, syrup and water. Cover pot; bring to boil over high heat about 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Once cooked, leave uncovered and boil an additional 1 minute.
Reduce heat to medium and boil until temperature reaches 230°.
Add peanuts; stir well with wooden spoon until mixture reaches 300° between 13 and 18 minutes.
Mixture should be golden brown.
Stir in butter until melted, then add baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour mixture in pan; will need to spread fast.
Allow to cool at least 1 hour, then turn out and break into pieces. Store in airtight container for several weeks.

title: joe case killer cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together all ingredients and pour into lightly greased baking pan.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shortbread
directions: Have oleo soft so it is workable.
Mix flour and sugar into oleo.
Take 1/2 mixture and knead until light and fluffy.
Pat out on lightly floured surface to thickness desired.
Cut into squares, dip top in sugar (this gives it a crust).
Prick bread with fork to allow the heat to go through.

title: coconut meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Beating at high speed, gradually sprinkle in sugar, 2 tbsp. at a time. Beating until sugar is completely dissolved.
(Whites should stand in stiff glossy peaks.)
With rubber spatula, fold in coconut & extract until mixed.

title: colonial popovers
directions: Blend the milk, oil and eggs with wire whip.
Combine salt and flour and add to the egg mixture, beating thoroughly.
Batter will be lumpy.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Grease heavy muffin or popover pans thoroughly, but do not flour.
Fill baking cups to top with batter and bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 20 minutes more.
Popovers should have a hollow sound when tapped and be brown all over.

title: potato soup
directions: In an 8 to 10-quart kettle, melt butter over mediuim heat; add onion and celery and cook, stirring occasionally until onion is very limp, about 10 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes, parsley, salt, pepper and chicken broth.
Cover.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in milk; cover.
Cook until soup is thoroughly hot but not boiling.
Blend cornstarch with water until smooth.
Add to soup.
Continue cooking until soup boils and thickens, about 5 minutes.

title: oven fried mustard chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Combine mustard and water.
Dip chicken in mustard mixture, then coat with crumb mixture.
Put in pan sprayed with Pam.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake until browned and cooked through, 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: georgia pecan meal cake
directions: Put all in large mixing bowl and beat 12 minutes.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour batter in and place in cold oven set at 300°. Cook 2 hours.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In small bowl combine marmalade and soy sauce; set aside. Preheat a wok or skillet over high heat.
Add half of the oil. Stir-fry beans for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add the mushrooms, pepper and onions.
Stir-fry 2 minutes or more until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables from wok; add remaining oil.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes or until done.
Return vegetables and add marmalade mixture.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Scald milk over low.
Add marshmallows and cook until smooth. Crush graham crackers and mix crumbs with remaining ingredients and add to marshmallow mix.
Blend well.
Line 2-quart bowl with wax paper and press in firmly. Serve when set.

title: spicy bread pudding
directions: Butter a baking pan.
Break up bread into pan.
In a bowl, mix all other ingredients except cinnamon and cheese.
Pour over bread, sprinkle with cinnamon and cheese and bake at 350° until medium brown.
Serve and enjoy!

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and spices.
Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.

Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir at least half of the hot mixture into egg yolks. Stir all into the mixture in saucepan. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in butter, vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut. Pour into pie shell. You may put meringue on top and brown or garnish with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft; add color and flavor (example: peppermint).
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar.
Knead the mixture until pie dough consistency (a soft or firmer candy can be made by adding or decreasing the amount of sugar).
Pinch off a small piece, form into a small marble sized ball and roll in granulated sugar.
Press the candy into a soft rubber mold and shape.
Remove excess and unmold at once onto waxed paper.
Makes 40 to 50 mints.

title: jello applesauce salad
directions: Cook the applesauce over low heat until sauce comes to a slow boil.
Add the powdered jello; mix well.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add the 7-Up, orange juice and orange peel; mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
This is really good.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and water.
Beat well.
Add jello, cake mix, then half of strawberries and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add icing.

title: grandma's casserole(weight watchers)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine; set aside. Brown ground meat for about 5 minutes; add all seasonings, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and mushrooms.
Stir in vegetables and simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon small amount of this sauce over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with noodles.
Cover with remaining sauce and top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into 8 servings. One serving equals 3 protein, 1 bread, 1/2 fat and 1 vegetable.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Cook, drain and mash enough potatoes to make 3 cups.
Season with butter, salt and pepper.
Shape into a mound on a pie pan. Whip 1/2 cup heavy cream until stiff; season with salt, paprika and a dash of cayenne.
Fold in 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Spread on potato mound.
Bake in preheated moderate oven, 375°, for about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch and Jell-O in cold water. Place on stove and bring to a good boil. Remove from stove and cool in refrigerator. Cut up strawberries. Sprinkle with sweetener. Put the strawberries in fridge and let sweeten. Fold strawberries into Jell-O glaze. Serve in dessert dishes or favorite pie crust.

title: butterhorns
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast into water.
Let stand for a few minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Pour hot milk over butter, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast, egg and half of flour.
Beat well.
Add enough more flour to make a dough that will not stick to bowl.
Turn out onto floured pastry cloth or board and knead lightly.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Divide dough in half; roll each half out on floured board to form a 12-inch circle.
Cut each into 12 pie shaped pieces.
Roll up from wide end and put pointed side down on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise for about 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Unraised dough can be refrigerated overnight; let stand at room temperature to soften enough to roll.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake until firm in a 350° oven.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water and add 1/2 cup sugar, egg, salt, melted shortening (cool) and 4 or more cups of flour.
Mix and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: pineapple cake with frosting
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add crushed pineapple and water.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to wet ingredients.
Mix well.
pour onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: "no bake" lemon cheese cake
directions: Melt butter in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Mix in crushed graham crackers and granulated sugar.
Press evenly in bottom of pan, reserving about 1/4 cup for topping.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt white chocolate chips and mix in peanut butter. Melt semi-sweet chocolate chips and barely stir into first mixture so as to leave a swirled effect. Pour into 9 x 13 pan and let set up.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Reduce heat to simmer 20 minutes. Stir in macaroni, chilies and half of the cheese. Stir in taco seasoning and the tomato sauce. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: remoulade sauce - patsy's
directions: Blend or process together in order the ingredients are listed. Refrigerate immediately.
Serve with cold boiled shrimp or crab. Recipe should not be kept more than four days.
Make only one recipe at a time.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inches).
Combine margarine, sugar, egg and mashed banana. Stir in flour and beat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: summer dessert
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Pour into individual glass dessert dishes (sherbet glasses are nice).
When Jell-O is firm, decorate with grapes, which have been chilled and frosted with sugar.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 1 tablespoon shortening in 9-inch iron skillet.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon cornmeal in skillet.
Return to oven and brown.
Mix all ingredients together.
Immediately pour mixture into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: avocado egg salad
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine eggs, bacon and onion. Carefully scoop out avocado halves, leaving firm shells; brush shells with a little lemon juice to prevent browning.
Mash avocado pulp.
In mixing bowl stir together the mayonnaise, 2 teaspoons lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add mashed avocado and egg mixture; spoon avocado-egg salad mixture into avocado shells.
Place filled avocados on individual lettuce-lined serving plates.
Garnish with bacon curl, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pepperoni swirls
directions: Thaw dough and let rise.
Grind pepperoni and mix with eggs. When dough has raised, cut into 4 parts and roll each part to make an oblong piece of dough.
Spread pepperoni and egg mixture onto the dough and roll like jelly roll.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into slices.
May be frozen and used at a later date.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Do not mix ingredients.
Pour butter in 8-inch square pan. Then layer graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips and pecans. Pour condensed milk over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat butter and shortening until light.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Combine 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.

title: broiled zucchini
directions: Parboil zucchini and cut in half.
Combine mayonnaise, Blue cheese and garlic salt.
Spread on top of zucchini.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until brown and bubbly about 7 to 10 minutes.

title: veggie stir-fry
directions: Heat large skillet over high heat; add olive oil and wait 10 seconds.
Add onion, garlic and peppers, stirring often.
When onion gets soft, turn heat down to medium and add bok choy or nappa.
Sprinkle entire dish with teriyaki sauce and cover, then turn heat down to low.
After 2 minutes, check to see if sticking. If so, add a little water and stir.
Cover and let simmer on low, about 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peanut butterscotch crunch
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter, then add potato sticks and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: low calorie cottage-tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on crackers, toast, English muffins, etc.

title: cabbage patch salad
directions: Chop cabbage.
Cut onions and put in the chopped cabbage. Toast almonds and sesame seed and add to cabbage and onions.
Put in refrigerator until next day.

title: zucchini boats
directions: *If avoiding oil, leave it out and use more zucchini.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the chocolate bark.
Add peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, salt and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Add flour and milk.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chowder
directions: Brown salt pork in olive oil in bottom of 5-quart kettle.
Add onion and simmer until clear.
Add water, potatoes and carrots. Cook until tender.
Add hot half and half, meat and seasoning and butter; use flour to thicken.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat sugar, oleo, butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add eggs and flour a little at a time, until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry fizz
directions: In glass pitcher or punch bowl, combine everything but ginger ale.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and stir gently.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: old fashioned tea cakes i(the kind grandmother tied in a pillow case)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, then add sifted dry ingredients with the first cup of flour.
Add milk and enough of the remaining flour to the proper consistency for rolling dough on floured board.
Cut in desired shapes.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° until lightly tanned.
Store in tight containers.

title: challah bread
directions: Early In The Day or Day Before:
In a bowl, combine sugar, salt, yeast and 1 cup flour.
In saucepan, heat oil and 3/4 cup water until very warm (125°).
With mixer at low speed, beat liquid into dry ingredients.
Beat at medium 2 minutes. Reserve 1 egg yolk.
To mixture in bowl, add egg whites, 2 eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes. Stir in 1 1/4 cups flour.
On floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes, working in about 1/4 cup flour.
Shape dough into a ball and place in greased bowl, turning dough to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: russian salad
directions: In a large bowl, marinate with French dressing the lettuce, onions and green beans.
Alternate layers of other ingredients, reserving 1 egg to be sliced for decorating top.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until its like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn out onto a floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Make 1/4-inch thick rectangle with dough.
Sprinkle apples and cinnamon evenly over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place in pan with butter.
Pour sugar syrup around rolls. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
May serve with ice cream.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl. Beat 4 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from sides of pan. Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove and cool on rack. Top with Sugar Glaze.

title: osgood pies
directions: Beat melted butter, sugar and egg yolks together; add other ingredients.
Fold in whites of eggs last.
Bake until set.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Boil sugar and corn syrup 30 seconds, no longer.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pork steak dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Add potatoes and onion.
Mix soup, mushrooms (with liquid), sherry, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
