Pour on pork, potatoes and onion. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until tender, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix vegetables with salt.
Put in a colander and drain 4 hours.
Heat vinegar, mustard seed and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Mix with drained vegetables.
Pack in pint jars and seal.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Add mayonnaise until moistened. Refrigerate.

title: molasses butterball cookies
directions: Beat margarine with electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds. Add molasses and beat until fluffy.
Add flour and beat until well blended at low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Roll 1 tablespoon dough into ball.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool. Gently roll cooled cookies in powdered sugar.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion, water chestnuts and peas in either a 9 x 12-inch serving dish or large serving bowl. Peas should be the top layer.
You can add any other salad ingredient to the layers: mushrooms, carrots, etc.

title: cauliflower and hamburger pie
directions: Fry hamburger.
Set aside in casserole dish.
In saucepan, boil cauliflower until tender.
When done, layer over hamburger. Combine butter, flour, milk and water.
Cook on low until thickened to gravy.
Pour over hamburger/cauliflower.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: super scalloped corn
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl, then pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes, until top is golden brown and inserted knife comes out clean.
If desired, sprinkle 1 cup shredded cheese on top the last 15 minutes of baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, adding just enough water or milk to hold together.
Form into 8 oval patties.
In a skillet, melt shortening.
When hot, brown patties on both sides; place in roasting pan.
Bring 4 cups of water to a boil in a large saucepan. Add the onion/soup mix; reduce heat and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Add mushroom soup, mix well and bring to a boil.
Pour over patties and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Wrap the sweet potato in foil and bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until soft.
Remove from oven and set aside. Lower oven temperature to 400°.
When cooled, peel and dice it.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Place livers in saucepan with enough water to cover.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Simmer, covered, for 12 to 15 minutes until livers are firm but tender.
Cool slightly for 15 minutes. Drain.
Process until smooth.
Add butter and process until fluffy. Add next 7 ingredients and process until blended.
Place in terrine (serving dish).
Chill, covered, until firm.
Serve with French bread or crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (approximately 5 minutes).
Drain off all water.
Place broccoli in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange slices of cheese on broccoli.
Spread the cream of celery soup on top of cheese slices.
Sprinkle the stuffing over the top.
Be sure to cover the edges also.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and cook onion until done and drain. Stir in pizza sauce and pasta. Transfer to 13 x 9 inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese and place pepperoni on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bacon.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients to meat.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country fried pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops and mushrooms with butter or oil. Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water, thyme, onion and carrots. Cover and cook on low for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over wide noodles.
(Easy to increase ingredients for more servings.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix.
Add soda, salt, vanilla and flour mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Chop onion and pepper over carrots.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over the carrots. Marinate overnight, covered.
Drain and serve.
May be served cold or warm.

title: play-doh(not edible)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add wet ingredients and stir over medium heat until thick.
Knead when cool.
You may add food coloring with wet ingredients.
Store in plastic container or plastic bag.
Will keep for several months.

title: italian dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake.

title: poppy seed coconut cake
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, pudding mix and poppy seeds; add water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow cake to cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing.
Drizzle with thin frosting glaze, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then top with grated cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: olive and cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses and butter.
Stir in olives and chives.
Chill slightly for easier shaping.
Form in ball on serving dish.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, sprinkle chopped nuts over ball. Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: possum waller breakfast pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cook sausage until done; crumble, then drain (or drain, then crumble). Sprinkle sausage in bottom of pie shell. Layer Swiss cheese on top. Sprinkle green onion on top. Lightly beat eggs in bowl. Add milk and beat lightly again. Pour egg mixture over sausage and cheese in pie shell. Place pie on cookie sheet in oven to catch any "overflow." Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Cool on rack for 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: santa claus cookies
directions: Mix
sugar, shortening, milk, lemon peel and egg.
Stir in flour,
baking
powder, baking soda and salt.
Heat oven to 400°. Shape
dough
into	1
1/4-inch
balls.
Place 2 inches apart
on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped
in	sugar.	Bake until edges are light brown for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix together flour and sugar.
Add to eggs; stir in pineapple and juice.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Spread melted margarine on top; do not stir.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Great served with ham.

title: ada's pound cake
directions: Grease tube pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Put in cold oven at 300°.
Cook for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool upside-down on bottle.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with chocolate icing.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix in order given and form into balls; brown. Top with soup. Simmer until done. Serve over spaghetti or rice.

title: pan pierogies
directions: Melt margarine and saute onions until clear.
Dice up cheese into the margarine mixture and heat on low until melted.
Boil lasagna noodles until tender (not overdone).
Cook potatoes according to directions.
Add cheese mixture to potatoes, stirring constantly, and add extra milk to make smooth and spreadable.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat eggs and salt together.
Then add to sugar mixture.
Add oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture. Refrigerate dough for 1 hour before rolling and cutting.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream oleo and cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add cake mix, half at a time.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: nova scotian plum loaf
directions: Combine boiling water, mashed potatoes and brown sugar.
Proof yeast and add to cooled potato mixture.
Add scalded milk, shortening and honey.
Add the amount of flours needed to make a sponge.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Add salt, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled (1 hour).
Divide into 4.
Roll out each loaf and sprinkle with a cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Roll up into loaves.
(Optional and recommended:
Let rise again.)
Bake for 65 minutes at 350°. Makes 4 loaves.

title: avgolemono soup(greek egg and lemon soup)
directions: Bring the broth to boil; add the rice.
Cook until done; turn the heat down.
Beat the eggs until light and foamy.
Add the lemon juice and beat some more.
Then add 1 cup of the hot soup and beat until well mixed.
Add the diluted egg and lemon mixture to the rest of the soup, beating constantly or the egg will curdle.
Heat almost to the boiling point, but not quite or the soup will curdle.
Serve hot or cold.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour and mix well.
Add juice and milk, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms.
Place 1/2 of asparagus in casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over asparagus and cover with egg slices.
Arrange remaining asparagus over eggs and sauce.
Top with almonds.

title: cottage cheese balls
directions: Form into balls; fry.
Put into casserole and cover with mushroom soup, thinned with a little milk.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: macaroni in a skillet
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.
Cook 3/4 to 1 cup macaroni.
When cooked, mix with sauce.

title: lemonade by the glass
directions: Cook water and sugar for 3 minutes to make a syrup.
For each serving, mix 3 to 4 tablespoons syrup with 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice and 1 cup water.
Store syrup in refrigerator.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole the cans of corn, butter (cut into small slices), eggs (slightly beaten), sugar, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir until blended, then crush fine the Ritz crackers and stir into the other ingredients.
You may save 1/3 cup crumbs to sprinkle on top for a prettier look.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until the corn is fairly stiff in the dish and golden brown.

title: kristen's yummy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water with a bay leaf.
When cold, peel and grate coarsely.
Put potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, oleo, sour cream, salt, pepper, onion and 1 cup cheese.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Cover and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
When finished baking, sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup potato chips.
Bake a few more minutes.

title: buffalo fire wings
directions: Fry wings in butter until brown, about 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients, toss with wings and put on large cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: instant baked potatoes
directions: Clean the potatoes thoroughly.
Puncture each with a fork. Put oven at 450°.
In the meantime, place the potatoes in microwave until 95% done.
Remove and put in hot oven to crisp the skins and finish baking.
This keeps you and kitchen cooler.

title: brown eyed susan cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and salt. Stir in flour. Chill for 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press a Kiss in center of each ball. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and cut apple into 8 pieces.
Take each crescent roll apart.
Put one piece of apple into big part of roll.
Roll up, put in pan.
Combine orange juice, sugar and butter in sauce pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: creme fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, salt and sugar.
Heat until boiling over medium heat; then time for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and immediately mix chocolate chips, vanilla and peanut butter or Marshmallow Creme until chips are melted.
Add nuts last.
Pour in a buttered dish and cool.

title: tangy carrots
directions: Place sliced carrots in a 2-quart saucepan; add 1/2 cup water and salt.
Cover and cook until steaming; lower heat and cook for 15 minutes until carrots are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir and cook for 5 minutes to glaze carrots.

title: snowballs(kids love these - mama and daddy do too!)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Blend in flour and nuts.
Form in balls of dough the size of walnuts.
Bake on cookie sheet in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butter pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
In a small mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all directions and pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Pecans will form top crust. Must be watched carefully.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well after each addition.
Add eggs gradually, beating until fluffy.
Fold in chopped pecans, corn syrup and salt.
Stir well.
Turn into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake another 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pie.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; set aside.
In large bowl, beat eggs thoroughly and add sugar. Continue to beat until eggs are lemon colored and fluffy. Gradually add the oil, pumpkin and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
At low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture, beating only until flour is moistened.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable soup
directions: In a 4-quart pot, cook margarine, carrots, onions, cabbage, parsley and salt over medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken broth, green beans (thawed) and caraway seed and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Serve hot over cubes of cheese.

title: jello salad
directions: Put the drained pineapple juice and strawberry juice in a 2-cup measuring cup.
Finish filling it with water.
Bring to a boil and dissolve jello in it.
When dissolved, add 2 more cups of cold water to jello.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add fruit and put in any container you like.

title: d's caramel apple blast
directions: In tea kettle, heat enough apple cider for a large coffee mug. While heating, pour caramel syrup into a large coffee mug. Fill with hot cider and top with Reddi-Wip.

title: raspberry fizz
directions: Mash the raspberries with a fork in a large bowl until they are well blended in their own juice.
Add the pineapple juice, ice cream and sherbet and stir well.
Slowly pour the cream soda into the ice cream mixture and stir well.
Pour into glasses and enjoy!

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine
in a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish with a cover. Add
all
the
other
ingredients and mix well.
Cook, covered, in a
350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir 2 or 3 times during the first 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thawed hash browns in greased casserole dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Sprinkel corn flakes over cheese mixture and drizzle melted margarine over corn flakes. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Core and slice tomatoes.
Combine with onions and green pepper.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and
bring	to
a boil.
Pack vegetables into clean, hot pint jars
leaving
1/2	inch
of
room at the top.
Pour hot liquid over vegetables.
Prepare lids according to manufacturers directions.
Wipe jar rims; adjust lid.
Process jars in a boiling water bath for 15 minutes.	Makes 8 pints.

title: potato-tomato bake
directions: Slice tomatoes approximately 3/4-inch thick.
Mound the potatoes in spoons on each slice of tomato.
Make a small indentation on top of potato mound and spoon 1/4 teaspoon margarine on top.
Sprinkle top of each potato-tomato with garlic salt or powder and thyme.
Bake in oven approximately 15 minutes at 400°. Different, but tasty.

title: applesauce
directions: Mix apples, water, cinnamon and sugar in pot.
Heat for two hours.
Mix well and serve.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Combine milk, water and butter in small saucepan. Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°). Butter does not need to melt. Place 3 1/2 cups of flour, sugar and yeast in bowl. Using dough hook, speed 2, mix 30 seconds. Gradually add warm liquids. Mix 1 minute longer. Continue on speed 2. Add remaining flour (1/2 cup at a time) until dough clings to hook and cleans sides of bowl (about 5 minutes). Knead on speed 2 or 3 for 5 minutes longer. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover. Let rise in warm place 15 minutes. Turn dough onto floured surface. Shape into rolls. Place on cookie sheet. Cover. Let rise in slightly warm oven (90°) 15 to 30 minutes. Bake in a 425° oven 12 minutes or until done. Cool on rack.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Line large casserole dish with crushed cornflakes.
Put 5 cups cabbage in dish (can cut large).
In a pan, mix margarine, milk, mayonnaise, water chestnuts and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage.
Put cheese on top, then cover with enough crushed cornflakes to cover top.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 7 week bran muffins
directions: In a small bowl, put bran flakes and stir in boiling water. Set aside.
In a huge mixing bowl cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Add buttermilk and soaked bran, stir. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Add all-bran and raisins/nuts.
Stir just until moistened.
Fill greased, "Pam-ed" or paper lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pone bread
directions: Scald meal thoroughly.
Add sugar, then flour and molasses, stirring all the time, using boiling water to thin until thin enough to pour easily.
Bake in greased pan for 2 hours at 300°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on a large jelly roll pan and cook according to package directions.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese mixture, mayonnaise and dressing with electric mixer.
Spread cheese mixture on the cooled crescent crust.
Top with vegetables, chill and serve.

title: hot dip
directions: Melt butter. Saute onion. Add cream cheese, mayonnaise and dried beef.
Heat until bubbly.
If using crab, add 2 more tablespoons of mayonnaise.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, salt and grated chocolate or cocoa.
Cover until boiling point is reached.
Boil to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Add flavoring and cool, without stirring, to room temperature.
Beat until mixture is creamy, thick and will hold its shape when dropped from a teaspoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or pour into well buttered, shallow pan and cut into squares.

title: fruit punch bars(no shortening in recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl at high speed.
Add fruit cocktail and juice and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Sprinkle with coconut and walnuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and top with glaze.

title: creole sauce(8 servings)
directions: Saute onion in butter; blend in the rest of the ingredients. Simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Serve with jambalaya, or add 2 cups cooked shrimp and serve over plain rice for Shrimp Creole.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix flour, sugar and dry yeast; add the egg, oil and water. Bake at 425° in muffin pans until golden brown.

title: easy pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease cookie sheet with butter or margarine.
Combine and stir nuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 6 minutes on High.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Add butter and cook 1 1/2 minutes on
High.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Then stir until foaming.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Then crack.
Store in an airtight container.

title: mother's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix as soft as you can handle.
Roll out thin and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake and frost when cool.

title: neckbone soup
directions: In a large pot, cover neckbones with water. Cook until well done. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat about 25 minutes.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Steam the beans until just tender.
(Larger beans will take longer than thinner ones.)
Remove from heat and immediately rinse in cold water.
While the beans are cooking, combine the dressing ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well to thoroughly combine.
Add the rinsed (well drained) beans to the dressing.
Add Swiss cheese. Toss until dressing is well distributed.
Cover tightly and marinate 2 to 3 hours, stirring about once an hour.
Add olives and sliced peppers.
Mix well, cover and chill overnight or at least 5 hours.
Serve topped with almonds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles.
Brown ground chuck and onion together. When meat is brown and onion is wilted, add tomato soup.
Fill soup can 1/2 full of ketchup and rest of can with water.
Add to meat mixture.
When noodles are cooked, drain and add to meat mixture.
Mix together and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except the grated cheese.
Pour half the batter into a large iron skillet which has been greased.
Sprinkle grated cheese over skillet mixture and add remaining batter.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple. When hot, add Jell-O. Stir until dissolved. Let cool. Put buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts in and stir. Mold and chill.

title: apple pie
directions: Stir together apples, spices, flour, sugar and raisins.
Put into a crust, then dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust. Make 3 cuts into crust.
Bake at 425° for about 40 to 50 minutes. When the juice begins to bubble and the crust is golden, the pie is done.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine melted shortening with sugar, add egg, beat together. Add dry ingredients together, sift.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Then add raisins.
Add 1/2 cup black walnuts.
Bake in load pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumpling casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
Add flour, sugar, salt, basil, pepper and broth; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Add peas and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken.
Pour into a greased 13x9x2 inch baking dish.

title: divinity
directions: In large saucepan, mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 255° or a hard ball is formed when a little is dropped into cold water. While this is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour sugar mixture into egg whites in a fine stream, beating constantly. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts, if wanted.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: clam dip
directions: Blend onions, parsley and oregano in a bowl.
Simmer clams with juice and lemon juice for 10 minutes.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
Combine all ingredients together except cheese. Place in baking dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
You can double this recipe.
Enjoy!!

title: tuna bunwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spoon mixture between bun halves. Wrap in foil. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. (Can be frozen.)

title: swedish apple coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Then add oil; mix well.
Then add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Stir in apple and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Frost with vanilla glaze when cool.
(Use cookie sheet.)

title: sister helen's scalloped potato and tuna casserole
directions: Heat butter in saucepan and saute onion about 5 minutes or until golden brown. Blend in flour and salt. Gradually stir in milk and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in tuna. Put potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole and pour tuna mixture over it. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Break chicken into small pieces and place in bottom of 13 x 9 baking dish.
Sprinkle chopped onion over chicken.
Place slices of velveeta cheese over onions.
Crush Dorito chips and sprinkle over cheese.
Mix together mushroom soup, chicken soup and Ro-tel. Pour over above layers.
Put a few Doritos on the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: 24 hour egg omelet
directions: Trim crust from bread slices and butter bread on 1 side.
Cut bread slices into cubes.
Place, butter side up, in 9 x 13-inch glass cake pan.
Beat eggs together with milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread cubes.
Add ham, then top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken on to boil. Next grease pan and spread rice in pan. Mix dried onion soup, mushroom soup and 1 can of water, together. Pour over rice and add chicken with shredded cheese on top. Cover with foil and cook for 30 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter; blend in flour and salt. Add broth all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add chicken and vegetables.
Heat until bubbling.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix cream-style corn, cornbread mix, eggs, sour cream and whole kernel corn.
Pour corn mixture into melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: california barbecue
directions: Boil noodles in salted water.
Place 1/2 noodles in baking dish; layer with spinach, cheese and pimentos.
Pour mushroom soup over all or you can layer soup also.
Place buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: barbara bush's barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer slowly for 45 minutes.
Taste for seasoning.
This sauce freezes well.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen semi-sweet soft cookies.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until done and brown on top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions omitting salt. Drain and place in large bowl.
Mix next 12 ingredients with macaroni.
Stir well.
Place in refrigerator and chill for at least 1 hour.
Keeps well if refrigerated.

title: orange baby carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Stir carrots around and pour in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion, garlic, olives and soup.
Place half of the Fritos in greased casserole dish and then pour in the hamburger mixture.
Pour chili over this.
Top with cheese and sprinkle rest of Fritos.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix with melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Freeze.
Soften ice cream; spread over crust. Freeze.

title: mom alice miller's grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate sweet potatoes or yams on a medium side of hand grater or in the blender.
Combine all of the ingredients (except eggs).
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour into shallow buttered baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bayou hash
directions: Slice onions and brown in fat.
Add ground rump and brown well.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over slow fire about 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple well.
Mix jello, cottage cheese, crushed pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip well.
Chill.

title: fried corn-on-the-cob
directions: Wet corn in water.
Salt and pepper each ear.
Dip in flour. Dip quickly in water and then in flour again.
Add 1 at a time to hot oil.
Cook until brown.
This corn needs no butter or margarine.
Serve in corn dishes with corn holders to make handling easier.

title: montana mountain muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients and stir into mixing bowl until dry ingredients are moistened.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to bake. Batter will keep for several weeks.
When ready, stir batter. Fill greased tins 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well!
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 150° for 15 minutes; 300° until done.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Melt butter; mix with flour and pecans.
Pat in bottom of 8-inch square pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; spread over crust.
Mix together pudding, 1 cup Cool Whip, pumpkin, milk, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and pumpkin pie spice.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over the top.

title: skyline chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix all ingredients and simmer.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook sausage; cook rice.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish. Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until hot.

title: pineapple-tapioca cream
directions: Pour pineapple juice into a 2-cup measure.
Add water to make 2 cups.
In saucepan, add sugar, tapioca and salt.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Stir in pineapple.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: tea garden salad
directions: Mix gelatin, water and tea.
Add oranges and pineapple. Congeal slightly.
Add chestnuts and set until firm.
Put whipped cream and grated orange rind on top.

title: festive hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas and spread on tortillas. Roll up and chill 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices and lay flat on serving platter for festive spiral hors d'oeuvres.

title: bo's dirty rice
directions: Cook rice; drain.
Cook sausage and onion; drain.
Add parsley and garlic powder.
Mix all together.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and raw peanuts in a 2-quart bowl suitable for microwave oven.
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir and cook 13 to 15 minutes (hard crack stage).
Stir twice in last minute.
Add butter, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break up.

title: easy rainbow punch
directions: Mix together sherbet and 3/4 of the Sprite.
Great for showers and parties!

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will keep for a long time in the refrigerator.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Boil 2 large potatoes.
Mash well.
Boil 2 cups water and add mashed potatoes.
Brown flour in butter, stirring constantly.
Add to potato mix.
Boil 3 minutes.
Grate Cheddar or Swiss cheese. Add slowly to potato mix turned to low.
Stir continuously as cheese melts.
Serve with grated onion on top.

title: polynesian cake
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Form into ball.
Leave plain or top with parsley flakes or paprika to make festive.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Mix limeade, lemonade, orange juice, 7-Up and whiskey in a large punch bowl.
For extra tangy flavor, add 3 packages whiskey sour cocktail mix.
Add orange slices, cherries and ice.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white with water; mix well with spices. Pour over pecans; toss until pecans are coated and bake until pecans are dry, about 1 hour at 250°. Stir to turn pecans.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Prepare sauce first by combining all ingredients except cornstarch.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch diluted in a little water.
Saute chicken in a little oil (do not brown), add all other ingredients and stir constantly.
Add sweet and sour sauce, salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy bisquick bars
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar and pecans.
Add beaten eggs.
Bake at 325°
for
to
35 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm. Bake in sheet cake pan.
Cool and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, nuts, squash and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: absolut kool-aid
directions: Pour Kool-Aid (flavor of choice) over ice.
Stir in vodka. Best after mowing the lawn.

title: pulled taffy
directions: Cool till it seems brittle when dropped in cold water.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla and 1/2 soda.
Mix and pour into well buttered platter and spread to edges.
Cool & pull till white & brittle.
Be sure hands are well buttered during pulling to prevent blisters.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Pour mixture over cereal and coat thoroughly.
Place sugar in heavy plastic bag.
Put 1/3 of cereal at a time in bag and shake until coated.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together.
Combine the apple mix and the flour mix; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or an hour.

title: country skillet bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8-inch cast-iron skillet well.
In large bowl combine muffin mix, wheat germ, cereal and sesame seed. In small bowl, using fork, beat milk and egg to blend.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Pour batter into prepared skillet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Place skillet on wire rack to cool completely; cut bread into wedges and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in casserole dish in 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pay day bars
directions: Combine yellow cake mix, 1 egg (beaten) and 1 stick margarine (melted). Spread in oblong 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Remove cake from oven and top with the marshmallows. Return to oven to melt marshmallows.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 1 1/2 cups syrup.
Combine butter, spices, marmalade and reserved syrup.
Bring to a boil; cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Reduce heat; gently stir in fruit.
Heat for 15 minutes.
Serves 6. Great to make ahead.
Stores well in refrigerator, but should be reheated to serve.

title: hawaiian chicken kabobs
directions: Drain apricots, reserving juice.
Quarter apricot halves.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Gradually add confectioners sugar.
Blend well; add vanilla.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Stir in condensed milk, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Pour into freezer can.
Add enough milk to fill can 3/4 full.
Let set 1 hour (I don't).

title: delicious pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in butter mixture alternately with egg nog; mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in pecans, raisins and cherries.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars well.
Add vanilla.
Beat and add eggs.
Add flour and baking soda; then add chips.
Batter should barely stick to finger.
Drop on ungreased pan and bake at 325° for 8 to 11 minutes, until golden brown.
They will not look done (this keeps them soft).
For variety, add other flavored chips.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Pour half corn bread crumbs in bottom of baking dish.
Add the squash mix and top with the rest of corn bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Stir ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Add to cabbage, carrot and onion.
Stir together for 5 minutes.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: edible cooked carrots
directions: Place all ingredients in pan.
Cook until done.

title: glazed apples and pork
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add pork chops and brown, about 5 minutes on each side.
Push chops to one side of skillet.
Combine honey and cranberry-orange relish in skillet.
Add apples and toss to coat with mixture. Cook about 5 minutes longer to heat apple mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in a little more than 1/3 cup butter; roll in potato chips seasoned with garlic salt.
Grease baking pan and arrange chicken in it.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Bake at 425° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: butterscotch bits and noodle candy
directions: Melt chips and bits in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add noodles.
Mix good and drop by small spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate 20 to 25 minutes.
When melting bits, don't get too hot.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients in pie tin.
Pat chicken breasts dry.
Roll in melted margarine.
Arrange in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle the dry mixture over the top of chicken.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, in 350° oven.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and roll into a ball. Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Let stand at room temperature about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with chopped walnuts. Chill for several hours.
This is also good using blueberry filling.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 340° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Extra good with or without whipped cream.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Stir flour, cornstarch and 1/4 cup sugar. Rub in butter with fingers until crumbly and no large particles remain.
Place in ungreased 8 or 9-inch round baking pan with a removeable bottom or in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Press firmly into an even layer. Along edges make an impression with a fork. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
While hot, cut into wedges.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: jean's pie crust
directions: Mix with hands or fork until crumbly, then press into pie pan to form crust.
Reserve 1/4 cup mixture to sprinkle on top of pie filling.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix together.
Melt 1 stick butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in pan over melted butter.
Take one or 2 cans of any fruit or pie filling; pour over batter.
Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes to 1 hour, at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and add cracker crumbs.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat 2 sticks butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs together for 20 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Add sliced bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Chill for 8 hours before serving.

title: do do balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, make into balls and put into refrigerator for 45 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cool crust and chill.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Chill slightly and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients.
Top with bacon strips.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy sauce pan, over medium heat, mix the sugar, milk and butter; stirring until sugar is dissolved. Cook to a soft boil. Add peanut butter and 2/3 of the jar of marshmallow creme, mixing well; add vanilla. Blend well and pour into a buttered 9 x 13 inch pan. When cooled, cut into squares.

title: herb cheese dip
directions: Mix at medium speed cheese, yogurt or milk, parsley, onion and tarragon until well blended.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes. Serve with raw vegetables.
